var book = {
	"name": "Joshua",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After the death of Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5853A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5853A\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5853B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5853B\"></sup> son of Nun, Moses’ aide:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Moses my servant is dead. Now then, you and all these people, get ready to cross the Jordan River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5854C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5854C\"></sup> into the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5854D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5854D\"></sup> I am about to give to them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5854E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5854E\"></sup>—to the Israelites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will give you every place where you set your foot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5855F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5855F\"></sup> as I promised Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5855G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5855G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Your territory will extend from the desert to Lebanon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5856H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5856H\"></sup> and from the great river, the Euphrates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5856I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5856I\"></sup>—all the Hittite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5856J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5856J\"></sup> country—to the Mediterranean Sea in the west.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5856K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5856K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>No one will be able to stand against you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5857L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5857L\"></sup> all the days of your life. As I was with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5857M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5857M\"></sup> Moses, so I will be with you; I will never leave you nor forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5857N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5857N\"></sup> you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Be strong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5858O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5858O\"></sup> and courageous,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5858P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5858P\"></sup> because you will lead these people to inherit the land I swore to their ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5858Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5858Q\"></sup> to give them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Be strong and very courageous. Be careful to obey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5859R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5859R\"></sup> all the law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5859S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5859S\"></sup> my servant Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5859T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5859T\"></sup> gave you; do not turn from it to the right or to the left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5859U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5859U\"></sup> that you may be successful wherever you go.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5859V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5859V\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Keep this Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5860W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5860W\"></sup> always on your lips;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5860X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5860X\"></sup> meditate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5860Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5860Y\"></sup> on it day and night, so that you may be careful to do everything written in it. Then you will be prosperous and successful.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5860Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5860Z\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5861AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5861AA\"></sup> do not be discouraged,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5861AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5861AB\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will be with you wherever you go.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5861AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5861AC\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Joshua ordered the officers of the people:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5862AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5862AD\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Go through the camp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5863AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5863AE\"></sup> and tell the people, ‘Get your provisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5863AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5863AF\"></sup> ready. Three days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5863AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5863AG\"></sup> from now you will cross the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5863AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5863AH\"></sup> here to go in and take possession<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5863AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5863AI\"></sup> of the land the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for your own.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But to the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5864AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5864AJ\"></sup> Joshua said,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Remember the command that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave you after he said, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give you rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5865AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5865AK\"></sup> by giving you this land.’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Your wives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5866AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5866AL\"></sup> your children and your livestock may stay in the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5866AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5866AM\"></sup> that Moses gave you east of the Jordan, but all your fighting men, ready for battle,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5866AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5866AN\"></sup> must cross over ahead of your fellow Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5866AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5866AO\"></sup> You are to help them",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives them rest, as he has done for you, and until they too have taken possession of the land the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving them. After that, you may go back and occupy your own land, which Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave you east of the Jordan toward the sunrise.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5867AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5867AP\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they answered Joshua, “Whatever you have commanded us we will do, and wherever you send us we will go.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5868AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5868AQ\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Just as we fully obeyed Moses, so we will obey you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5869AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5869AR\"></sup> Only may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God be with you as he was with Moses.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whoever rebels against your word and does not obey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5870AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5870AS\"></sup> it, whatever you may command them, will be put to death. Only be strong and courageous!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5870AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5870AT\"></sup>”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Then Joshua son of Nun secretly sent two spies<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5871A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5871A\"></sup> from Shittim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5871B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5871B\"></sup> “Go, look over<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5871C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5871C\"></sup> the land,” he said, “especially Jericho.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5871D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5871D\"></sup>” So they went and entered the house of a prostitute named Rahab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5871E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5871E\"></sup> and stayed there.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king of Jericho was told, “Look, some of the Israelites have come here tonight to spy out the land.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the king of Jericho sent this message to Rahab:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5873F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5873F\"></sup> “Bring out the men who came to you and entered your house, because they have come to spy out the whole land.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the woman had taken the two men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5874G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5874G\"></sup> and hidden them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5874H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5874H\"></sup> She said, “Yes, the men came to me, but I did not know where they had come from.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>At dusk, when it was time to close the city gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5875I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5875I\"></sup> they left. I don’t know which way they went. Go after them quickly. You may catch up with them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5875J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5875J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(But she had taken them up to the roof and hidden them under the stalks of flax<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5876K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5876K\"></sup> she had laid out on the roof.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5876L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5876L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the men set out in pursuit of the spies on the road that leads to the fords of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5877M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5877M\"></sup> and as soon as the pursuers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5877N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5877N\"></sup> had gone out, the gate was shut.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Before the spies lay down for the night, she went up on the roof<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5878O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5878O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and said to them, “I know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you this land and that a great fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5879P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5879P\"></sup> of you has fallen on us, so that all who live in this country are melting in fear because of you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>We have heard how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dried up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5880Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5880Q\"></sup> the water of the Red Sea for you when you came out of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5880R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5880R\"></sup> and what you did to Sihon and Og,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5880S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5880S\"></sup> the two kings of the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5880T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5880T\"></sup> east of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5880U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5880U\"></sup> whom you completely destroyed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5880V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5880V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When we heard of it, our hearts melted in fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5881W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5881W\"></sup> and everyone’s courage failed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5881X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5881X\"></sup> because of you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5881Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5881Y\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5881Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5881Z\"></sup> is God in heaven above and on the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5881AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5881AA\"></sup> below.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Now then, please swear to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5882AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5882AB\"></sup> by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that you will show kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5882AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5882AC\"></sup> to my family, because I have shown kindness to you. Give me a sure sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5882AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5882AD\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>that you will spare the lives of my father and mother, my brothers and sisters, and all who belong to them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5883AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5883AE\"></sup>—and that you will save us from death.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Our lives for your lives!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5884AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5884AF\"></sup> the men assured her. “If you don’t tell what we are doing, we will treat you kindly and faithfully<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5884AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5884AG\"></sup> when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives us the land.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So she let them down by a rope<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5885AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5885AH\"></sup> through the window,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5885AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5885AI\"></sup> for the house she lived in was part of the city wall.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>She said to them, “Go to the hills<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5886AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5886AJ\"></sup> so the pursuers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5886AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5886AK\"></sup> will not find you. Hide yourselves there three days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5886AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5886AL\"></sup> until they return, and then go on your way.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5886AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5886AM\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the men had said to her, “This oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5887AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5887AN\"></sup> you made us swear will not be binding on us",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>unless, when we enter the land, you have tied this scarlet cord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5888AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5888AO\"></sup> in the window<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5888AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5888AP\"></sup> through which you let us down, and unless you have brought your father and mother, your brothers and all your family<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5888AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5888AQ\"></sup> into your house.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If any of them go outside your house into the street, their blood will be on their own heads;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5889AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5889AR\"></sup> we will not be responsible. As for those who are in the house with you, their blood will be on our head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5889AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5889AS\"></sup> if a hand is laid on them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if you tell what we are doing, we will be released from the oath you made us swear.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5890AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5890AT\"></sup>”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Agreed,” she replied. “Let it be as you say.”So she sent them away, and they departed. And she tied the scarlet cord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5891AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5891AU\"></sup> in the window.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5891AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5891AV\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When they left, they went into the hills and stayed there three days,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5892AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5892AW\"></sup> until the pursuers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5892AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5892AX\"></sup> had searched all along the road and returned without finding them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the two men started back. They went down out of the hills, forded the river and came to Joshua son of Nun and told him everything that had happened to them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They said to Joshua, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has surely given the whole land into our hands;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5894AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5894AY\"></sup> all the people are melting in fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5894AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5894AZ\"></sup> because of us.”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Early in the morning Joshua and all the Israelites set out from Shittim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5895A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5895A\"></sup> and went to the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5895B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5895B\"></sup> where they camped before crossing over.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>After three days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5896C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5896C\"></sup> the officers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5896D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5896D\"></sup> went throughout the camp,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5896E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5896E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>giving orders to the people: “When you see the ark of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5897F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5897F\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and the Levitical<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5897G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5897G\"></sup> priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5897H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5897H\"></sup> carrying it, you are to move out from your positions and follow it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then you will know which way to go, since you have never been this way before. But keep a distance of about two thousand cubits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5898I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5898I\"></sup> between you and the ark; do not go near it.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Joshua told the people, “Consecrate yourselves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5899J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5899J\"></sup> for tomorrow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do amazing things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5899K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5899K\"></sup> among you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Joshua said to the priests, “Take up the ark of the covenant and pass on ahead of the people.” So they took it up and went ahead of them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Today I will begin to exalt you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5901L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5901L\"></sup> in the eyes of all Israel, so they may know that I am with you as I was with Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5901M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5901M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Tell the priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5902N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5902N\"></sup> who carry the ark of the covenant: ‘When you reach the edge of the Jordan’s waters, go and stand in the river.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joshua said to the Israelites, “Come here and listen to the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This is how you will know that the living God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5904O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5904O\"></sup> is among you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5904P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5904P\"></sup> and that he will certainly drive out before you the Canaanites, Hittites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5904Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5904Q\"></sup> Hivites, Perizzites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5904R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5904R\"></sup> Girgashites, Amorites and Jebusites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5904S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5904S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>See, the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5905T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5905T\"></sup> will go into the Jordan ahead of you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5905U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5905U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now then, choose twelve men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5906V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5906V\"></sup> from the tribes of Israel, one from each tribe.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And as soon as the priests who carry the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the Lord of all the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5907W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5907W\"></sup>—set foot in the Jordan, its waters flowing downstream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5907X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5907X\"></sup> will be cut off<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5907Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5907Y\"></sup> and stand up in a heap.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5907Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5907Z\"></sup>”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So when the people broke camp to cross the Jordan, the priests carrying the ark of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5908AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5908AA\"></sup> went ahead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5908AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5908AB\"></sup> of them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5909AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5909AC\"></sup> is at flood stage<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5909AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5909AD\"></sup> all during harvest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5909AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5909AE\"></sup> Yet as soon as the priests who carried the ark reached the Jordan and their feet touched the water’s edge,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the water from upstream stopped flowing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AF\"></sup> It piled up in a heap<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AG\"></sup> a great distance away, at a town called Adam in the vicinity of Zarethan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AH\"></sup> while the water flowing down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AI\"></sup> to the Sea of the Arabah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AJ\"></sup> (that is, the Dead Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AK\"></sup>) was completely cut off.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AL\"></sup> So the people crossed over opposite Jericho.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5910AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5910AM\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5911AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5911AN\"></sup> who carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stopped in the middle of the Jordan and stood on dry ground,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5911AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5911AO\"></sup> while all Israel passed by until the whole nation had completed the crossing on dry ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5911AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5911AP\"></sup>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When the whole nation had finished crossing the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5912A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5912A\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Choose twelve men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5913B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5913B\"></sup> from among the people, one from each tribe,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and tell them to take up twelve stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5914C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5914C\"></sup> from the middle of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5914D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5914D\"></sup> from right where the priests are standing, and carry them over with you and put them down at the place where you stay tonight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5914E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5914E\"></sup>”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Joshua called together the twelve men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5915F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5915F\"></sup> he had appointed from the Israelites, one from each tribe,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and said to them, “Go over before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God into the middle of the Jordan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5916G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5916G\"></sup> Each of you is to take up a stone on his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the Israelites,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>to serve as a sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5917H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5917H\"></sup> among you. In the future, when your children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5917I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5917I\"></sup> ask you, ‘What do these stones mean?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5917J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5917J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>tell them that the flow of the Jordan was cut off<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5918K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5918K\"></sup> before the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. When it crossed the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. These stones are to be a memorial<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5918L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5918L\"></sup> to the people of Israel forever.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the Israelites did as Joshua commanded them. They took twelve stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5919M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5919M\"></sup> from the middle of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5919N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5919N\"></sup> according to the number of the tribes of the Israelites, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told Joshua;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5919O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5919O\"></sup> and they carried them over with them to their camp, where they put them down.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joshua set up the twelve stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5920P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5920P\"></sup> that had been in the middle of the Jordan at the spot where the priests who carried the ark of the covenant had stood. And they are there to this day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5920Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5920Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the priests who carried the ark remained standing in the middle of the Jordan until everything the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Joshua was done by the people, just as Moses had directed Joshua. The people hurried over,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and as soon as all of them had crossed, the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the priests came to the other side while the people watched.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The men of Reuben,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5923R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5923R\"></sup> Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5923S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5923S\"></sup> and the half-tribe of Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5923T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5923T\"></sup> crossed over, ready for battle, in front of the Israelites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5923U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5923U\"></sup> as Moses had directed them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5923V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5923V\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>About forty thousand armed for battle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5924W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5924W\"></sup> crossed over<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5924X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5924X\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the plains of Jericho for war.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>That day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> exalted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5925Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5925Y\"></sup> Joshua in the sight of all Israel; and they stood in awe of him all the days of his life, just as they had stood in awe of Moses.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Command the priests carrying the ark of the covenant law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5927Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5927Z\"></sup> to come up out of the Jordan.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Joshua commanded the priests, “Come up out of the Jordan.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the priests came up out of the river carrying the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. No sooner had they set their feet on the dry ground than the waters of the Jordan returned to their place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5929AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5929AA\"></sup> and ran at flood stage<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5929AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5929AB\"></sup> as before.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>On the tenth day of the first month the people went up from the Jordan and camped at Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5930AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5930AC\"></sup> on the eastern border of Jericho.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Joshua set up at Gilgal the twelve stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5931AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5931AD\"></sup> they had taken out of the Jordan.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He said to the Israelites, “In the future when your descendants ask their parents, ‘What do these stones mean?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5932AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5932AE\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>tell them, ‘Israel crossed the Jordan on dry ground.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5933AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5933AF\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God dried up the Jordan before you until you had crossed over. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did to the Jordan what he had done to the Red Sea when he dried it up before us until we had crossed over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5934AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5934AG\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He did this so that all the peoples of the earth might know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5935AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5935AH\"></sup> that the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is powerful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5935AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5935AI\"></sup> and so that you might always fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5935AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5935AJ\"></sup>”"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now when all the Amorite kings west of the Jordan and all the Canaanite kings along the coast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5936A\"></sup> heard how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had dried up the Jordan before the Israelites until they had crossed over, their hearts melted in fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5936B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5936B\"></sup> and they no longer had the courage to face the Israelites.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At that time the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Make flint knives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5937C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5937C\"></sup> and circumcise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5937D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5937D\"></sup> the Israelites again.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Joshua made flint knives and circumcised the Israelites at Gibeath Haaraloth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now this is why he did so: All those who came out of Egypt—all the men of military age<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5939E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5939E\"></sup>—died in the wilderness on the way after leaving Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5939F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5939F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All the people that came out had been circumcised, but all the people born in the wilderness during the journey from Egypt had not.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Israelites had moved about in the wilderness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5941G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5941G\"></sup> forty years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5941H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5941H\"></sup> until all the men who were of military age when they left Egypt had died, since they had not obeyed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had sworn to them that they would not see the land he had solemnly promised their ancestors to give us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5941I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5941I\"></sup> a land flowing with milk and honey.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5941J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5941J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he raised up their sons in their place, and these were the ones Joshua circumcised. They were still uncircumcised because they had not been circumcised on the way.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And after the whole nation had been circumcised, they remained where they were in camp until they were healed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5943K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5943K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Today I have rolled away the reproach of Egypt from you.” So the place has been called Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5944L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5944L\"></sup> to this day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On the evening of the fourteenth day of the month,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5945M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5945M\"></sup> while camped at Gilgal on the plains of Jericho, the Israelites celebrated the Passover.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5945N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5945N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The day after the Passover, that very day, they ate some of the produce of the land:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5946O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5946O\"></sup> unleavened bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5946P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5946P\"></sup> and roasted grain.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5946Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5946Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The manna stopped the day after they ate this food from the land; there was no longer any manna for the Israelites, but that year they ate the produce of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5947R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5947R\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now when Joshua was near Jericho, he looked up and saw a man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5948S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5948S\"></sup> standing in front of him with a drawn sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5948T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5948T\"></sup> in his hand. Joshua went up to him and asked, “Are you for us or for our enemies?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Neither,” he replied, “but as commander of the army of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> I have now come.” Then Joshua fell facedown<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5949U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5949U\"></sup> to the ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5949V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5949V\"></sup> in reverence, and asked him, “What message does my Lord have for his servant?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The commander of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s army replied, “Take off your sandals, for the place where you are standing is holy.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5950W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5950W\"></sup> And Joshua did so."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now the gates of Jericho<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5951A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5951A\"></sup> were securely barred because of the Israelites. No one went out and no one came in.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “See, I have delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5952B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5952B\"></sup> Jericho into your hands, along with its king and its fighting men.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>March around the city once with all the armed men. Do this for six days.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Have seven priests carry trumpets of rams’ horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5954C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5954C\"></sup> in front of the ark. On the seventh day, march around the city seven times, with the priests blowing the trumpets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5954D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5954D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When you hear them sound a long blast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5955E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5955E\"></sup> on the trumpets, have the whole army give a loud shout;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5955F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5955F\"></sup> then the wall of the city will collapse and the army will go up, everyone straight in.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Joshua son of Nun called the priests and said to them, “Take up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have seven priests carry trumpets in front of it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5956G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5956G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he ordered the army, “Advance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5957H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5957H\"></sup>! March around the city, with an armed guard going ahead of the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5957I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5957I\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Joshua had spoken to the people, the seven priests carrying the seven trumpets before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went forward, blowing their trumpets, and the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant followed them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The armed guard marched ahead of the priests who blew the trumpets, and the rear guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5959J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5959J\"></sup> followed the ark. All this time the trumpets were sounding.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Joshua had commanded the army, “Do not give a war cry, do not raise your voices, do not say a word until the day I tell you to shout. Then shout!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5960K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5960K\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So he had the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> carried around the city, circling it once. Then the army returned to camp and spent the night there.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joshua got up early the next morning and the priests took up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The seven priests carrying the seven trumpets went forward, marching before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and blowing the trumpets. The armed men went ahead of them and the rear guard followed the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, while the trumpets kept sounding.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So on the second day they marched around the city once and returned to the camp. They did this for six days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>On the seventh day, they got up at daybreak and marched around the city seven times in the same manner, except that on that day they circled the city seven times.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5965L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5965L\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The seventh time around, when the priests sounded the trumpet blast, Joshua commanded the army, “Shout! For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you the city!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5966M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5966M\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The city and all that is in it are to be devoted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5967N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5967N\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Only Rahab the prostitute<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5967O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5967O\"></sup> and all who are with her in her house shall be spared, because she hid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5967P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5967P\"></sup> the spies we sent.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But keep away from the devoted things,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5968Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5968Q\"></sup> so that you will not bring about your own destruction by taking any of them. Otherwise you will make the camp of Israel liable to destruction<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5968R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5968R\"></sup> and bring trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5968S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5968S\"></sup> on it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>All the silver and gold and the articles of bronze and iron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5969T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5969T\"></sup> are sacred to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and must go into his treasury.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When the trumpets sounded,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5970U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5970U\"></sup> the army shouted, and at the sound of the trumpet, when the men gave a loud shout,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5970V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5970V\"></sup> the wall collapsed; so everyone charged straight in, and they took the city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5970W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5970W\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They devoted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5971X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5971X\"></sup> the city to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and destroyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5971Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5971Y\"></sup> with the sword every living thing in it—men and women, young and old, cattle, sheep and donkeys.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Joshua said to the two men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5972Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5972Z\"></sup> who had spied out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5972AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5972AA\"></sup> the land, “Go into the prostitute’s house and bring her out and all who belong to her, in accordance with your oath to her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5972AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5972AB\"></sup>”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So the young men who had done the spying went in and brought out Rahab, her father and mother, her brothers and sisters and all who belonged to her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5973AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5973AC\"></sup> They brought out her entire family and put them in a place outside the camp of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then they burned the whole city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5974AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5974AD\"></sup> and everything in it, but they put the silver and gold and the articles of bronze and iron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5974AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5974AE\"></sup> into the treasury of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5974AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5974AF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Joshua spared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5975AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5975AG\"></sup> Rahab the prostitute,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5975AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5975AH\"></sup> with her family and all who belonged to her, because she hid the men Joshua had sent as spies to Jericho<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5975AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5975AI\"></sup>—and she lives among the Israelites to this day.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>At that time Joshua pronounced this solemn oath:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5976AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5976AJ\"></sup> “Cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5976AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5976AK\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is the one who undertakes to rebuild this city, Jericho:“At the cost of his firstborn sonhe will lay its foundations;at the cost of his youngesthe will set up its gates.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5976AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5976AL\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joshua,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5977AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5977AM\"></sup> and his fame spread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5977AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5977AN\"></sup> throughout the land."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>But the Israelites were unfaithful in regard to the devoted things;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5978A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5978A\"></sup> Achan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5978B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5978B\"></sup> son of Karmi, the son of Zimri, the son of Zerah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5978C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5978C\"></sup> of the tribe of Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5978D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5978D\"></sup> took some of them. So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5978E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5978E\"></sup> against Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5978F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5978F\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5979G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5979G\"></sup> which is near Beth Aven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5979H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5979H\"></sup> to the east of Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5979I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5979I\"></sup> and told them, “Go up and spy out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5979J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5979J\"></sup> the region.” So the men went up and spied out Ai.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When they returned to Joshua, they said, “Not all the army will have to go up against Ai. Send two or three thousand men to take it and do not weary the whole army, for only a few people live there.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So about three thousand went up; but they were routed by the men of Ai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5981K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5981K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>who killed about thirty-six<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5982L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5982L\"></sup> of them. They chased the Israelites from the city gate as far as the stone quarries and struck them down on the slopes. At this the hearts of the people melted in fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5982M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5982M\"></sup> and became like water.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Joshua tore his clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5983N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5983N\"></sup> and fell facedown<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5983O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5983O\"></sup> to the ground before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, remaining there till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5983P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5983P\"></sup> The elders of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5983Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5983Q\"></sup> did the same, and sprinkled dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5983R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5983R\"></sup> on their heads.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Joshua said, “Alas, Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, why<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5984S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5984S\"></sup> did you ever bring this people across the Jordan to deliver us into the hands of the Amorites to destroy us?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5984T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5984T\"></sup> If only we had been content to stay on the other side of the Jordan!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Pardon your servant, Lord. What can I say, now that Israel has been routed by its enemies?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Canaanites and the other people of the country will hear about this and they will surround us and wipe out our name from the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5986U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5986U\"></sup> What then will you do for your own great name?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5986V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5986V\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Stand up! What are you doing down on your face?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Israel has sinned;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5988W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5988W\"></sup> they have violated my covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5988X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5988X\"></sup> which I commanded them to keep. They have taken some of the devoted things; they have stolen, they have lied,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5988Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5988Y\"></sup> they have put them with their own possessions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5988Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5988Z\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>That is why the Israelites cannot stand against their enemies;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5989AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5989AA\"></sup> they turn their backs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5989AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5989AB\"></sup> and run<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5989AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5989AC\"></sup> because they have been made liable to destruction.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5989AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5989AD\"></sup> I will not be with you anymore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5989AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5989AE\"></sup> unless you destroy whatever among you is devoted to destruction.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Go, consecrate the people. Tell them, ‘Consecrate yourselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5990AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5990AF\"></sup> in preparation for tomorrow; for this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: There are devoted things among you, Israel. You cannot stand against your enemies until you remove them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘In the morning, present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5991AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5991AG\"></sup> yourselves tribe by tribe. The tribe the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5991AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5991AH\"></sup> shall come forward clan by clan; the clan the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses shall come forward family by family; and the family the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses shall come forward man by man.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Whoever is caught with the devoted things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5992AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5992AI\"></sup> shall be destroyed by fire,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5992AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5992AJ\"></sup> along with all that belongs to him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5992AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5992AK\"></sup> He has violated the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5992AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5992AL\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and has done an outrageous thing in Israel!’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5992AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5992AM\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Early the next morning Joshua had Israel come forward by tribes, and Judah was chosen.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The clans of Judah came forward, and the Zerahites were chosen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5994AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5994AN\"></sup> He had the clan of the Zerahites come forward by families, and Zimri was chosen.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joshua had his family come forward man by man, and Achan son of Karmi, the son of Zimri, the son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5995AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5995AO\"></sup> was chosen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5995AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5995AP\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Joshua said to Achan, “My son, give glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5996AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5996AQ\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and honor him. Tell<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5996AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5996AR\"></sup> me what you have done; do not hide it from me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Achan replied, “It is true! I have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel. This is what I have done:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When I saw in the plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5998AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5998AS\"></sup> a beautiful robe from Babylonia, two hundred shekels of silver and a bar of gold weighing fifty shekels, I coveted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5998AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5998AT\"></sup> them and took them. They are hidden in the ground inside my tent, with the silver underneath.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent, and there it was, hidden in his tent, with the silver underneath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They took the things from the tent, brought them to Joshua and all the Israelites and spread them out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Joshua, together with all Israel, took Achan son of Zerah, the silver, the robe, the gold bar, his sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6001AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6001AU\"></sup> and daughters, his cattle, donkeys and sheep, his tent and all that he had, to the Valley of Achor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6001AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6001AV\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Joshua said, “Why have you brought this trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6002AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6002AW\"></sup> on us? The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring trouble on you today.”Then all Israel stoned him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6002AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6002AX\"></sup> and after they had stoned the rest, they burned them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6002AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6002AY\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Over Achan they heaped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6003AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6003AZ\"></sup> up a large pile of rocks, which remains to this day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6003BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6003BA\"></sup> Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned from his fierce anger.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6003BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6003BB\"></sup> Therefore that place has been called the Valley of Achor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6003BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6003BC\"></sup> ever since."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Do not be afraid;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6004A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6004A\"></sup> do not be discouraged.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6004B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6004B\"></sup> Take the whole army<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6004C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6004C\"></sup> with you, and go up and attack Ai.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6004D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6004D\"></sup> For I have delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6004E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6004E\"></sup> into your hands the king of Ai, his people, his city and his land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall do to Ai and its king as you did to Jericho and its king, except that you may carry off their plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6005F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6005F\"></sup> and livestock for yourselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6005G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6005G\"></sup> Set an ambush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6005H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6005H\"></sup> behind the city.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Joshua and the whole army moved out to attack Ai. He chose thirty thousand of his best fighting men and sent them out at night",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>with these orders: “Listen carefully. You are to set an ambush behind the city. Don’t go very far from it. All of you be on the alert.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I and all those with me will advance on the city, and when the men come out against us, as they did before, we will flee from them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They will pursue us until we have lured them away from the city, for they will say, ‘They are running away from us as they did before.’ So when we flee from them,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>you are to rise up from ambush and take the city. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give it into your hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6010I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6010I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When you have taken the city, set it on fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6011J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6011J\"></sup> Do what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6011K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6011K\"></sup> See to it; you have my orders.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Joshua sent them off, and they went to the place of ambush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6012L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6012L\"></sup> and lay in wait between Bethel and Ai, to the west of Ai—but Joshua spent that night with the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Early the next morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6013M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6013M\"></sup> Joshua mustered his army, and he and the leaders of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6013N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6013N\"></sup> marched before them to Ai.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The entire force that was with him marched up and approached the city and arrived in front of it. They set up camp north of Ai, with the valley between them and the city.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joshua had taken about five thousand men and set them in ambush between Bethel and Ai, to the west of the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the soldiers took up their positions—with the main camp to the north of the city and the ambush to the west of it. That night Joshua went into the valley.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When the king of Ai saw this, he and all the men of the city hurried out early in the morning to meet Israel in battle at a certain place overlooking the Arabah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6017O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6017O\"></sup> But he did not know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6017P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6017P\"></sup> that an ambush had been set against him behind the city.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Joshua and all Israel let themselves be driven back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6018Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6018Q\"></sup> before them, and they fled toward the wilderness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6018R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6018R\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All the men of Ai were called to pursue them, and they pursued Joshua and were lured away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6019S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6019S\"></sup> from the city.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Not a man remained in Ai or Bethel who did not go after Israel. They left the city open and went in pursuit of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Hold out toward Ai the javelin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6021T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6021T\"></sup> that is in your hand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6021U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6021U\"></sup> for into your hand I will deliver the city.” So Joshua held out toward the city the javelin that was in his hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6021V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6021V\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As soon as he did this, the men in the ambush rose quickly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6022W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6022W\"></sup> from their position and rushed forward. They entered the city and captured it and quickly set it on fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6022X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6022X\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The men of Ai looked back and saw the smoke of the city rising up into the sky,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6023Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6023Y\"></sup> but they had no chance to escape in any direction; the Israelites who had been fleeing toward the wilderness had turned back against their pursuers.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For when Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had taken the city and that smoke was going up from it, they turned around<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6024Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6024Z\"></sup> and attacked the men of Ai.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Those in the ambush also came out of the city against them, so that they were caught in the middle, with Israelites on both sides. Israel cut them down, leaving them neither survivors nor fugitives.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6025AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6025AA\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But they took the king of Ai alive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6026AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6026AB\"></sup> and brought him to Joshua.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Israel had finished killing all the men of Ai in the fields and in the wilderness where they had chased them, and when every one of them had been put to the sword, all the Israelites returned to Ai and killed those who were in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Twelve thousand men and women fell that day—all the people of Ai.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6028AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6028AC\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For Joshua did not draw back the hand that held out his javelin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6029AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6029AD\"></sup> until he had destroyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6029AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6029AE\"></sup> all who lived in Ai.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6029AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6029AF\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Israel did carry off for themselves the livestock and plunder of this city, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had instructed Joshua.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6030AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6030AG\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Joshua burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6031AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6031AH\"></sup> Ai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6031AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6031AI\"></sup> and made it a permanent heap of ruins,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6031AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6031AJ\"></sup> a desolate place to this day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6031AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6031AK\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He impaled the body of the king of Ai on a pole and left it there until evening. At sunset,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6032AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6032AL\"></sup> Joshua ordered them to take the body from the pole and throw it down at the entrance of the city gate. And they raised a large pile of rocks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6032AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6032AM\"></sup> over it, which remains to this day.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Joshua built on Mount Ebal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6033AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6033AN\"></sup> an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6033AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6033AO\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded the Israelites. He built it according to what is written in the Book of the Law of Moses—an altar of uncut stones, on which no iron tool<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6034AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6034AP\"></sup> had been used. On it they offered to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burnt offerings and sacrificed fellowship offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6034AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6034AQ\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>There, in the presence of the Israelites, Joshua wrote on stones a copy of the law of Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6035AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6035AR\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>All the Israelites, with their elders, officials and judges, were standing on both sides of the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, facing the Levitical<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6036AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6036AS\"></sup> priests who carried it. Both the foreigners living among them and the native-born<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6036AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6036AT\"></sup> were there. Half of the people stood in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them in front of Mount Ebal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6036AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6036AU\"></sup> as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had formerly commanded when he gave instructions to bless the people of Israel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Afterward, Joshua read all the words of the law—the blessings and the curses—just as it is written in the Book of the Law.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6037AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6037AV\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>There was not a word of all that Moses had commanded that Joshua did not read to the whole assembly of Israel, including the women and children, and the foreigners who lived among them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6038AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6038AW\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now when all the kings west of the Jordan heard about these things—the kings in the hill country,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6039A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6039A\"></sup> in the western foothills, and along the entire coast of the Mediterranean Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6039B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6039B\"></sup> as far as Lebanon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6039C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6039C\"></sup> (the kings of the Hittites, Amorites, Canaanites, Perizzites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6039D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6039D\"></sup> Hivites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6039E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6039E\"></sup> and Jebusites)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6039F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6039F\"></sup>—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>they came together to wage war against Joshua and Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>However, when the people of Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6041G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6041G\"></sup> heard what Joshua had done to Jericho and Ai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6041H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6041H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>they resorted to a ruse: They went as a delegation whose donkeys were loaded with worn-out sacks and old wineskins, cracked and mended.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They put worn and patched sandals on their feet and wore old clothes. All the bread of their food supply was dry and moldy.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then they went to Joshua in the camp at Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6044I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6044I\"></sup> and said to him and the Israelites, “We have come from a distant country;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6044J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6044J\"></sup> make a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6044K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6044K\"></sup> with us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Israelites said to the Hivites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6045L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6045L\"></sup> “But perhaps you live near us, so how can we make a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6045M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6045M\"></sup> with you?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“We are your servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6046N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6046N\"></sup>” they said to Joshua.But Joshua asked, “Who are you and where do you come from?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They answered: “Your servants have come from a very distant country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6047O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6047O\"></sup> because of the fame of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. For we have heard reports<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6047P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6047P\"></sup> of him: all that he did in Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6047Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6047Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and all that he did to the two kings of the Amorites east of the Jordan—Sihon king of Heshbon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6048R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6048R\"></sup> and Og king of Bashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6048S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6048S\"></sup> who reigned in Ashtaroth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6048T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6048T\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And our elders and all those living in our country said to us, ‘Take provisions for your journey; go and meet them and say to them, “We are your servants; make a treaty with us.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>This bread of ours was warm when we packed it at home on the day we left to come to you. But now see how dry and moldy it is.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And these wineskins that we filled were new, but see how cracked they are. And our clothes and sandals are worn out by the very long journey.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Israelites sampled their provisions but did not inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6052U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6052U\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Joshua made a treaty of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6053V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6053V\"></sup> with them to let them live,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6053W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6053W\"></sup> and the leaders of the assembly ratified it by oath.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Three days after they made the treaty with the Gibeonites, the Israelites heard that they were neighbors, living near<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6054X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6054X\"></sup> them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So the Israelites set out and on the third day came to their cities: Gibeon, Kephirah, Beeroth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6055Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6055Y\"></sup> and Kiriath Jearim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6055Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6055Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the Israelites did not attack them, because the leaders of the assembly had sworn an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6056AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6056AA\"></sup> to them by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.The whole assembly grumbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6056AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6056AB\"></sup> against the leaders,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>but all the leaders answered, “We have given them our oath by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and we cannot touch them now.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>This is what we will do to them: We will let them live, so that God’s wrath will not fall on us for breaking the oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6058AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6058AC\"></sup> we swore to them.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They continued, “Let them live,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6059AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6059AD\"></sup> but let them be woodcutters and water carriers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6059AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6059AE\"></sup> in the service of the whole assembly.” So the leaders’ promise to them was kept.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Joshua summoned the Gibeonites and said, “Why did you deceive us by saying, ‘We live a long way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6060AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6060AF\"></sup> from you,’ while actually you live near<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6060AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6060AG\"></sup> us?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You are now under a curse:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6061AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6061AH\"></sup> You will never be released from service as woodcutters and water carriers for the house of my God.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They answered Joshua, “Your servants were clearly told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6062AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6062AI\"></sup> how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God had commanded his servant Moses to give you the whole land and to wipe out all its inhabitants from before you. So we feared for our lives because of you, and that is why we did this.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>We are now in your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6063AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6063AJ\"></sup> Do to us whatever seems good and right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6063AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6063AK\"></sup> to you.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So Joshua saved them from the Israelites, and they did not kill them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>That day he made the Gibeonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6065AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6065AL\"></sup> woodcutters and water carriers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6065AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6065AM\"></sup> for the assembly, to provide for the needs of the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the place the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would choose.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6065AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6065AN\"></sup> And that is what they are to this day."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now Adoni-Zedek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6066A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6066A\"></sup> king of Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6066B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6066B\"></sup> heard that Joshua had taken Ai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6066C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6066C\"></sup> and totally destroyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6066D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6066D\"></sup> it, doing to Ai and its king as he had done to Jericho and its king, and that the people of Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6066E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6066E\"></sup> had made a treaty of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6066F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6066F\"></sup> with Israel and had become their allies.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He and his people were very much alarmed at this, because Gibeon was an important city, like one of the royal cities; it was larger than Ai, and all its men were good fighters.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem appealed to Hoham king of Hebron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6068G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6068G\"></sup> Piram king of Jarmuth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6068H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6068H\"></sup> Japhia king of Lachish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6068I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6068I\"></sup> and Debir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6068J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6068J\"></sup> king of Eglon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6068K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6068K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Come up and help me attack Gibeon,” he said, “because it has made peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6069L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6069L\"></sup> with Joshua and the Israelites.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the five kings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6070M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6070M\"></sup> of the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6070N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6070N\"></sup>—the kings of Jerusalem, Hebron, Jarmuth, Lachish and Eglon—joined forces. They moved up with all their troops and took up positions against Gibeon and attacked it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Gibeonites then sent word to Joshua in the camp at Gilgal:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6071O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6071O\"></sup> “Do not abandon your servants. Come up to us quickly and save us! Help us, because all the Amorite kings from the hill country have joined forces against us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joshua marched up from Gilgal with his entire army,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6072P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6072P\"></sup> including all the best fighting men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Do not be afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6073Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6073Q\"></sup> of them; I have given them into your hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6073R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6073R\"></sup> Not one of them will be able to withstand you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6073S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6073S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After an all-night march from Gilgal, Joshua took them by surprise.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> threw them into confusion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6075T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6075T\"></sup> before Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6075U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6075U\"></sup> so Joshua and the Israelites defeated them completely at Gibeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6075V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6075V\"></sup> Israel pursued them along the road going up to Beth Horon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6075W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6075W\"></sup> and cut them down all the way to Azekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6075X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6075X\"></sup> and Makkedah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6075Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6075Y\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As they fled before Israel on the road down from Beth Horon to Azekah, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hurled large hailstones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6076Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6076Z\"></sup> down on them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6076AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6076AA\"></sup> and more of them died from the hail than were killed by the swords of the Israelites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>On the day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6077AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6077AB\"></sup> over to Israel, Joshua said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of Israel:“Sun, stand still over Gibeon,and you, moon, over the Valley of Aijalon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6077AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6077AC\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the sun stood still,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6078AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6078AD\"></sup>and the moon stopped,till the nation avenged itself on its enemies,as it is written in the Book of Jashar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6078AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6078AE\"></sup>The sun stopped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6078AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6078AF\"></sup> in the middle of the sky and delayed going down about a full day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There has never been a day like it before or since, a day when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to a human being. Surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was fighting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6079AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6079AG\"></sup> for Israel!",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Joshua returned with all Israel to the camp at Gilgal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6080AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6080AH\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now the five kings had fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6081AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6081AI\"></sup> and hidden in the cave at Makkedah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Joshua was told that the five kings had been found hiding in the cave at Makkedah,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>he said, “Roll large rocks up to the mouth of the cave, and post some men there to guard it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But don’t stop; pursue your enemies! Attack them from the rear and don’t let them reach their cities, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given them into your hand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Joshua and the Israelites defeated them completely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6085AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6085AJ\"></sup> but a few survivors managed to reach their fortified cities.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6085AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6085AK\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The whole army then returned safely to Joshua in the camp at Makkedah, and no one uttered a word against the Israelites.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Joshua said, “Open the mouth of the cave and bring those five kings out to me.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So they brought the five kings out of the cave—the kings of Jerusalem, Hebron, Jarmuth, Lachish and Eglon.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When they had brought these kings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6089AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6089AL\"></sup> to Joshua, he summoned all the men of Israel and said to the army commanders who had come with him, “Come here and put your feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6089AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6089AM\"></sup> on the necks of these kings.” So they came forward and placed their feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6089AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6089AN\"></sup> on their necks.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Joshua said to them, “Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged. Be strong and courageous.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6090AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6090AO\"></sup> This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do to all the enemies you are going to fight.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Joshua put the kings to death and exposed their bodies on five poles, and they were left hanging on the poles until evening.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>At sunset<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6092AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6092AP\"></sup> Joshua gave the order and they took them down from the poles and threw them into the cave where they had been hiding. At the mouth of the cave they placed large rocks, which are there to this day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6092AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6092AQ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>That day Joshua took Makkedah. He put the city and its king to the sword and totally destroyed everyone in it. He left no survivors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6093AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6093AR\"></sup> And he did to the king of Makkedah as he had done to the king of Jericho.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6093AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6093AS\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him moved on from Makkedah to Libnah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6094AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6094AT\"></sup> and attacked it.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also gave that city and its king into Israel’s hand. The city and everyone in it Joshua put to the sword. He left no survivors there. And he did to its king as he had done to the king of Jericho.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him moved on from Libnah to Lachish;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6096AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6096AU\"></sup> he took up positions against it and attacked it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Lachish into Israel’s hands, and Joshua took it on the second day. The city and everyone in it he put to the sword, just as he had done to Libnah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Meanwhile, Horam king of Gezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6098AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6098AV\"></sup> had come up to help Lachish, but Joshua defeated him and his army—until no survivors were left.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him moved on from Lachish to Eglon;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6099AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6099AW\"></sup> they took up positions against it and attacked it.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They captured it that same day and put it to the sword and totally destroyed everyone in it, just as they had done to Lachish.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him went up from Eglon to Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6101AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6101AX\"></sup> and attacked it.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They took the city and put it to the sword, together with its king, its villages and everyone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6102AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6102AY\"></sup> in it. They left no survivors. Just as at Eglon, they totally destroyed it and everyone in it.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him turned around and attacked Debir.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6103AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6103AZ\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They took the city, its king and its villages, and put them to the sword. Everyone in it they totally destroyed. They left no survivors. They did to Debir and its king as they had done to Libnah and its king and to Hebron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6104BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6104BA\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So Joshua subdued the whole region, including the hill country, the Negev,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6105BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6105BB\"></sup> the western foothills and the mountain slopes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6105BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6105BC\"></sup> together with all their kings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6105BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6105BD\"></sup> He left no survivors. He totally destroyed all who breathed, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, had commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6105BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6105BE\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Joshua subdued them from Kadesh Barnea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6106BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6106BF\"></sup> to Gaza<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6106BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6106BG\"></sup> and from the whole region of Goshen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6106BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6106BH\"></sup> to Gibeon.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>All these kings and their lands Joshua conquered in one campaign, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, fought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6107BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6107BI\"></sup> for Israel.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then Joshua returned with all Israel to the camp at Gilgal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6108BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6108BJ\"></sup>"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>When Jabin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6109A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6109A\"></sup> king of Hazor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6109B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6109B\"></sup> heard of this, he sent word to Jobab king of Madon, to the kings of Shimron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6109C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6109C\"></sup> and Akshaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6109D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6109D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and to the northern kings who were in the mountains, in the Arabah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6110E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6110E\"></sup> south of Kinnereth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6110F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6110F\"></sup> in the western foothills and in Naphoth Dor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6110G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6110G\"></sup> on the west;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>to the Canaanites in the east and west; to the Amorites, Hittites, Perizzites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6111H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6111H\"></sup> and Jebusites in the hill country;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6111I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6111I\"></sup> and to the Hivites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6111J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6111J\"></sup> below Hermon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6111K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6111K\"></sup> in the region of Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6111L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6111L\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They came out with all their troops and a large number of horses and chariots—a huge army, as numerous as the sand on the seashore.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6112M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6112M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All these kings joined forces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6113N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6113N\"></sup> and made camp together at the Waters of Merom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6113O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6113O\"></sup> to fight against Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Do not be afraid of them, because by this time tomorrow I will hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6114P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6114P\"></sup> all of them, slain, over to Israel. You are to hamstring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6114Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6114Q\"></sup> their horses and burn their chariots.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6114R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6114R\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joshua and his whole army came against them suddenly at the Waters of Merom and attacked them,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into the hand of Israel. They defeated them and pursued them all the way to Greater Sidon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6116S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6116S\"></sup> to Misrephoth Maim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6116T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6116T\"></sup> and to the Valley of Mizpah on the east, until no survivors were left.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joshua did to them as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had directed: He hamstrung their horses and burned their chariots.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At that time Joshua turned back and captured Hazor and put its king to the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6118U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6118U\"></sup> (Hazor had been the head of all these kingdoms.)",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Everyone in it they put to the sword. They totally destroyed them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6119V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6119V\"></sup> not sparing anyone that breathed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6119W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6119W\"></sup> and he burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6119X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6119X\"></sup> Hazor itself.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joshua took all these royal cities and their kings and put them to the sword. He totally destroyed them, as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6120Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6120Y\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet Israel did not burn any of the cities built on their mounds—except Hazor, which Joshua burned.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Israelites carried off for themselves all the plunder and livestock of these cities, but all the people they put to the sword until they completely destroyed them, not sparing anyone that breathed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6122Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6122Z\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded his servant Moses, so Moses commanded Joshua, and Joshua did it; he left nothing undone of all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6123AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6123AA\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Joshua took this entire land: the hill country,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6124AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6124AB\"></sup> all the Negev,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6124AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6124AC\"></sup> the whole region of Goshen, the western foothills,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6124AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6124AD\"></sup> the Arabah and the mountains of Israel with their foothills,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>from Mount Halak, which rises toward Seir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6125AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6125AE\"></sup> to Baal Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6125AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6125AF\"></sup> in the Valley of Lebanon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6125AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6125AG\"></sup> below Mount Hermon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6125AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6125AH\"></sup> He captured all their kings and put them to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6125AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6125AI\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joshua waged war against all these kings for a long time.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Except for the Hivites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6127AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6127AJ\"></sup> living in Gibeon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6127AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6127AK\"></sup> not one city made a treaty of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6127AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6127AL\"></sup> with the Israelites, who took them all in battle.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For it was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself who hardened their hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6128AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6128AM\"></sup> to wage war against Israel, so that he might destroy them totally, exterminating them without mercy, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6128AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6128AN\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>At that time Joshua went and destroyed the Anakites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6129AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6129AO\"></sup> from the hill country: from Hebron, Debir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6129AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6129AP\"></sup> and Anab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6129AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6129AQ\"></sup> from all the hill country of Judah, and from all the hill country of Israel. Joshua totally destroyed them and their towns.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>No Anakites were left in Israelite territory; only in Gaza,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6130AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6130AR\"></sup> Gath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6130AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6130AS\"></sup> and Ashdod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6130AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6130AT\"></sup> did any survive.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Joshua took the entire land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6131AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6131AU\"></sup> just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had directed Moses, and he gave it as an inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6131AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6131AV\"></sup> to Israel according to their tribal divisions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6131AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6131AW\"></sup> Then the land had rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6131AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6131AX\"></sup> from war.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6131AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6131AY\"></sup>"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>These are the kings of the land whom the Israelites had defeated and whose territory they took<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6132A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6132A\"></sup> over east of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6132B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6132B\"></sup> from the Arnon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6132C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6132C\"></sup> Gorge to Mount Hermon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6132D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6132D\"></sup> including all the eastern side of the Arabah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6132E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6132E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6133F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6133F\"></sup>He ruled from Aroer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6133G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6133G\"></sup> on the rim of the Arnon Gorge—from the middle of the gorge—to the Jabbok River,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6133H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6133H\"></sup> which is the border of the Ammonites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6133I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6133I\"></sup> This included half of Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6133J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6133J\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He also ruled over the eastern Arabah from the Sea of Galilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6134K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6134K\"></sup> to the Sea of the Arabah (that is, the Dead Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6134L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6134L\"></sup>), to Beth Jeshimoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6134M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6134M\"></sup> and then southward below the slopes of Pisgah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6134N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6134N\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the territory of Og king of Bashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6135O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6135O\"></sup> one of the last of the Rephaites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6135P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6135P\"></sup> who reigned in Ashtaroth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6135Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6135Q\"></sup> and Edrei.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He ruled over Mount Hermon, Salekah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6136R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6136R\"></sup> all of Bashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6136S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6136S\"></sup> to the border of the people of Geshur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6136T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6136T\"></sup> and Maakah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6136U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6136U\"></sup> and half of Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6136V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6136V\"></sup> to the border of Sihon king of Heshbon.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moses, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the Israelites conquered them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6137W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6137W\"></sup> And Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave their land to the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh to be their possession.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6137X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6137X\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Here is a list of the kings of the land that Joshua and the Israelites conquered on the west side of the Jordan, from Baal Gad in the Valley of Lebanon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6138Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6138Y\"></sup> to Mount Halak, which rises toward Seir. Joshua gave their lands as an inheritance to the tribes of Israel according to their tribal divisions.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The lands included the hill country, the western foothills, the Arabah, the mountain slopes, the wilderness and the Negev.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6139Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6139Z\"></sup> These were the lands of the Hittites, Amorites, Canaanites, Perizzites, Hivites and Jebusites. These were the kings:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6139AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6139AA\"></sup>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>When Joshua had grown old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6156A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6156A\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “You are now very old, and there are still very large areas of land to be taken over.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“This is the land that remains: all the regions of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6157B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6157B\"></sup> and Geshurites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6157C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6157C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>from the Shihor River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6158D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6158D\"></sup> on the east of Egypt to the territory of Ekron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6158E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6158E\"></sup> on the north, all of it counted as Canaanite though held by the five Philistine rulers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6158F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6158F\"></sup> in Gaza, Ashdod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6158G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6158G\"></sup> Ashkelon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6158H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6158H\"></sup> Gath and Ekron; the territory of the Avvites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6158I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6158I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>on the south; all the land of the Canaanites, from Arah of the Sidonians as far as Aphek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6159J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6159J\"></sup> and the border of the Amorites;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6159K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6159K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the area of Byblos;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6160L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6160L\"></sup> and all Lebanon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6160M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6160M\"></sup> to the east, from Baal Gad below Mount Hermon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6160N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6160N\"></sup> to Lebo Hamath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6160O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6160O\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“As for all the inhabitants of the mountain regions from Lebanon to Misrephoth Maim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6161P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6161P\"></sup> that is, all the Sidonians, I myself will drive them out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6161Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6161Q\"></sup> before the Israelites. Be sure to allocate this land to Israel for an inheritance, as I have instructed you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6161R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6161R\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and divide it as an inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6162S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6162S\"></sup> among the nine tribes and half of the tribe of Manasseh.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The other half of Manasseh, the Reubenites and the Gadites had received the inheritance that Moses had given them east of the Jordan, as he, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, had assigned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6163T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6163T\"></sup> it to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6163U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6163U\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It extended from Aroer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6164V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6164V\"></sup> on the rim of the Arnon Gorge, and from the town in the middle of the gorge, and included the whole plateau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6164W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6164W\"></sup> of Medeba as far as Dibon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6164X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6164X\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and all the towns of Sihon king of the Amorites, who ruled in Heshbon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6165Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6165Y\"></sup> out to the border of the Ammonites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6165Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6165Z\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It also included Gilead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6166AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6166AA\"></sup> the territory of the people of Geshur and Maakah, all of Mount Hermon and all Bashan as far as Salekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6166AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6166AB\"></sup>—",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>that is, the whole kingdom of Og in Bashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6167AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6167AC\"></sup> who had reigned in Ashtaroth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6167AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6167AD\"></sup> and Edrei.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6167AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6167AE\"></sup> (He was the last of the Rephaites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6167AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6167AF\"></sup>) Moses had defeated them and taken over their land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6167AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6167AG\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the Israelites did not drive out the people of Geshur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6168AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6168AH\"></sup> and Maakah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6168AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6168AI\"></sup> so they continue to live among the Israelites to this day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6168AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6168AJ\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But to the tribe of Levi he gave no inheritance, since the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, are their inheritance, as he promised them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6169AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6169AK\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>This is what Moses had given to the tribe of Reuben, according to its clans:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The territory from Aroer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6171AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6171AL\"></sup> on the rim of the Arnon Gorge, and from the town in the middle of the gorge, and the whole plateau past Medeba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6171AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6171AM\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>to Heshbon and all its towns on the plateau,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6172AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6172AN\"></sup> including Dibon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6172AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6172AO\"></sup> Bamoth Baal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6172AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6172AP\"></sup> Beth Baal Meon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6172AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6172AQ\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jahaz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6173AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6173AR\"></sup> Kedemoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6173AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6173AS\"></sup> Mephaath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6173AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6173AT\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Kiriathaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6174AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6174AU\"></sup> Sibmah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6174AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6174AV\"></sup> Zereth Shahar on the hill in the valley,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Beth Peor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6175AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6175AW\"></sup> the slopes of Pisgah, and Beth Jeshimoth—",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>all the towns on the plateau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6176AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6176AX\"></sup> and the entire realm of Sihon king of the Amorites, who ruled at Heshbon. Moses had defeated him and the Midianite chiefs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6176AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6176AY\"></sup> Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur and Reba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6176AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6176AZ\"></sup>—princes allied with Sihon—who lived in that country.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In addition to those slain in battle, the Israelites had put to the sword Balaam son of Beor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6177BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6177BA\"></sup> who practiced divination.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6177BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6177BB\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The boundary of the Reubenites was the bank of the Jordan. These towns and their villages were the inheritance of the Reubenites, according to their clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6178BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6178BC\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>This is what Moses had given to the tribe of Gad, according to its clans:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The territory of Jazer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6180BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6180BD\"></sup> all the towns of Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6180BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6180BE\"></sup> and half the Ammonite country as far as Aroer, near Rabbah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6180BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6180BF\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and from Heshbon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6181BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6181BG\"></sup> to Ramath Mizpah and Betonim, and from Mahanaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6181BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6181BH\"></sup> to the territory of Debir;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6181BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6181BI\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and in the valley, Beth Haram, Beth Nimrah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6182BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6182BJ\"></sup> Sukkoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6182BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6182BK\"></sup> and Zaphon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6182BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6182BL\"></sup> with the rest of the realm of Sihon king of Heshbon (the east side of the Jordan, the territory up to the end of the Sea of Galilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6182BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6182BM\"></sup>).",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>These towns and their villages were the inheritance of the Gadites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6183BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6183BN\"></sup> according to their clans.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>This is what Moses had given to the half-tribe of Manasseh, that is, to half the family of the descendants of Manasseh, according to its clans:",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The territory extending from Mahanaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6185BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6185BO\"></sup> and including all of Bashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6185BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6185BP\"></sup> the entire realm of Og king of Bashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6185BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6185BQ\"></sup>—all the settlements of Jair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6185BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6185BR\"></sup> in Bashan, sixty towns,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>half of Gilead, and Ashtaroth and Edrei (the royal cities of Og in Bashan).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6186BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6186BS\"></sup> This was for the descendants of Makir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6186BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6186BT\"></sup> son of Manasseh—for half of the sons of Makir, according to their clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6186BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6186BU\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This is the inheritance Moses had given when he was in the plains of Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6187BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6187BV\"></sup> across the Jordan east of Jericho.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6187BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6187BW\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But to the tribe of Levi, Moses had given no inheritance;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6188BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6188BX\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, is their inheritance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6188BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6188BY\"></sup> as he promised them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6188BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6188BZ\"></sup>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Now these are the areas the Israelites received as an inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6189A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6189A\"></sup> in the land of Canaan, which Eleazar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6189B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6189B\"></sup> the priest, Joshua son of Nun and the heads of the tribal clans of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6189C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6189C\"></sup> allotted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6189D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6189D\"></sup> to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6189E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6189E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Their inheritances were assigned by lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6190F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6190F\"></sup> to the nine and a half tribes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6190G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6190G\"></sup> as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moses had granted the two and a half tribes their inheritance east of the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6191H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6191H\"></sup> but had not granted the Levites an inheritance among the rest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6191I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6191I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for Joseph’s descendants had become two tribes—Manasseh and Ephraim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6192J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6192J\"></sup> The Levites received no share of the land but only towns to live in, with pasturelands for their flocks and herds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6192K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6192K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the Israelites divided the land, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6193L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6193L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now the people of Judah approached Joshua at Gilgal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6194M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6194M\"></sup> and Caleb son of Jephunneh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6194N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6194N\"></sup> the Kenizzite said to him, “You know what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses the man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6194O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6194O\"></sup> at Kadesh Barnea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6194P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6194P\"></sup> about you and me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6194Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6194Q\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent me from Kadesh Barnea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6195R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6195R\"></sup> to explore the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6195S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6195S\"></sup> And I brought him back a report according to my convictions,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6195T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6195T\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>but my fellow Israelites who went up with me made the hearts of the people melt in fear.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6196U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6196U\"></sup> I, however, followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God wholeheartedly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6196V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6196V\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So on that day Moses swore to me, ‘The land on which your feet have walked will be your inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6197W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6197W\"></sup> and that of your children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6197X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6197X\"></sup> forever, because you have followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God wholeheartedly.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Now then, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6198Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6198Y\"></sup> he has kept me alive for forty-five years since the time he said this to Moses, while Israel moved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6198Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6198Z\"></sup> about in the wilderness. So here I am today, eighty-five years old!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6198AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6198AA\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I am still as strong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6199AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6199AB\"></sup> today as the day Moses sent me out; I’m just as vigorous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6199AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6199AC\"></sup> to go out to battle now as I was then.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now give me this hill country that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised me that day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6200AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6200AD\"></sup> You yourself heard then that the Anakites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6200AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6200AE\"></sup> were there and their cities were large and fortified,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6200AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6200AF\"></sup> but, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helping me, I will drive them out just as he said.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Joshua blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6201AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6201AG\"></sup> Caleb son of Jephunneh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6201AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6201AH\"></sup> and gave him Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6201AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6201AI\"></sup> as his inheritance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6201AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6201AJ\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Hebron has belonged to Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite ever since, because he followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, wholeheartedly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6202AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6202AK\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>(Hebron used to be called Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6203AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6203AL\"></sup> after Arba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6203AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6203AM\"></sup> who was the greatest man among the Anakites.)Then the land had rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6203AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6203AN\"></sup> from war."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The allotment for the tribe of Judah, according to its clans, extended down to the territory of Edom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6204B\"></sup> to the Desert of Zin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6204C\"></sup> in the extreme south.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6204D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6204D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Their southern boundary started from the bay at the southern end of the Dead Sea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6205E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6205E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>crossed south of Scorpion Pass,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6206F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6206F\"></sup> continued on to Zin and went over to the south of Kadesh Barnea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6206G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6206G\"></sup> Then it ran past Hezron up to Addar and curved around to Karka.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It then passed along to Azmon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6207H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6207H\"></sup> and joined the Wadi of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6207I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6207I\"></sup> ending at the Mediterranean Sea. This is their southern boundary.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The eastern boundary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6208J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6208J\"></sup> is the Dead Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6208K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6208K\"></sup> as far as the mouth of the Jordan.The northern boundary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6208L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6208L\"></sup> started from the bay of the sea at the mouth of the Jordan,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>went up to Beth Hoglah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6209M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6209M\"></sup> and continued north of Beth Arabah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6209N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6209N\"></sup> to the Stone of Bohan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6209O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6209O\"></sup> son of Reuben.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The boundary then went up to Debir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6210P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6210P\"></sup> from the Valley of Achor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6210Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6210Q\"></sup> and turned north to Gilgal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6210R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6210R\"></sup> which faces the Pass of Adummim south of the gorge. It continued along to the waters of En Shemesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6210S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6210S\"></sup> and came out at En Rogel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6210T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6210T\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then it ran up the Valley of Ben Hinnom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6211U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6211U\"></sup> along the southern slope of the Jebusite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6211V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6211V\"></sup> city (that is, Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6211W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6211W\"></sup>). From there it climbed to the top of the hill west of the Hinnom Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6211X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6211X\"></sup> at the northern end of the Valley of Rephaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6211Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6211Y\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>From the hilltop the boundary headed toward the spring of the waters of Nephtoah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6212Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6212Z\"></sup> came out at the towns of Mount Ephron and went down toward Baalah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6212AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6212AA\"></sup> (that is, Kiriath Jearim).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6212AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6212AB\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then it curved westward from Baalah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6213AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6213AC\"></sup> to Mount Seir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6213AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6213AD\"></sup> ran along the northern slope of Mount Jearim (that is, Kesalon), continued down to Beth Shemesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6213AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6213AE\"></sup> and crossed to Timnah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6213AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6213AF\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It went to the northern slope of Ekron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6214AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6214AG\"></sup> turned toward Shikkeron, passed along to Mount Baalah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6214AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6214AH\"></sup> and reached Jabneel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6214AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6214AI\"></sup> The boundary ended at the sea.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The western boundary is the coastline of the Mediterranean Sea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6215AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6215AJ\"></sup>These are the boundaries around the people of Judah by their clans.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In accordance with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command to him, Joshua gave to Caleb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6216AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6216AK\"></sup> son of Jephunneh a portion in Judah—Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6216AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6216AL\"></sup>, that is, Hebron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6216AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6216AM\"></sup> (Arba was the forefather of Anak.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6216AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6216AN\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From Hebron Caleb drove out the three Anakites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6217AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6217AO\"></sup>—Sheshai, Ahiman and Talmai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6217AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6217AP\"></sup> the sons of Anak.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6217AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6217AQ\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>From there he marched against the people living in Debir (formerly called Kiriath Sepher).",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Caleb said, “I will give my daughter Aksah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6219AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6219AR\"></sup> in marriage to the man who attacks and captures Kiriath Sepher.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Othniel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6220AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6220AS\"></sup> son of Kenaz, Caleb’s brother, took it; so Caleb gave his daughter Aksah to him in marriage.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>One day when she came to Othniel, she urged him to ask her father for a field. When she got off her donkey, Caleb asked her, “What can I do for you?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>She replied, “Do me a special favor. Since you have given me land in the Negev,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6222AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6222AT\"></sup> give me also springs of water.” So Caleb gave her the upper and lower springs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6222AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6222AU\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>This is the inheritance of the tribe of Judah, according to its clans:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The southernmost towns of the tribe of Judah in the Negev<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6224AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6224AV\"></sup> toward the boundary of Edom were:Kabzeel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6224AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6224AW\"></sup> Eder,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6224AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6224AX\"></sup> Jagur,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Kedesh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6226AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6226AY\"></sup> Hazor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6226AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6226AZ\"></sup> Ithnan,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Ziph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6227BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6227BA\"></sup> Telem, Bealoth,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Hazor Hadattah, Kerioth Hezron (that is, Hazor),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6228BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6228BB\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Amam, Shema, Moladah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6229BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6229BC\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Hazar Gaddah, Heshmon, Beth Pelet,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Hazar Shual,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6231BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6231BD\"></sup> Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6231BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6231BE\"></sup> Biziothiah,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Baalah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6232BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6232BF\"></sup> Iyim, Ezem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6232BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6232BG\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Eltolad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6233BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6233BH\"></sup> Kesil, Hormah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6233BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6233BI\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6234BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6234BJ\"></sup> Madmannah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6234BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6234BK\"></sup> Sansannah,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6235BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6235BL\"></sup> and Rimmon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6235BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6235BM\"></sup>—a total of twenty-nine towns and their villages.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the western foothills:Eshtaol,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6236BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6236BN\"></sup> Zorah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6236BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6236BO\"></sup> Ashnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6236BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6236BP\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Zanoah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6237BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6237BQ\"></sup> En Gannim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6237BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6237BR\"></sup> Tappuah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6237BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6237BS\"></sup> Enam,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jarmuth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6238BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6238BT\"></sup> Adullam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6238BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6238BU\"></sup> Sokoh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6238BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6238BV\"></sup> Azekah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6238BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6238BW\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Shaaraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6239BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6239BX\"></sup> Adithaim and Gederah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6239BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6239BY\"></sup> (or Gederothaim)—fourteen towns and their villages.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal Gad,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Dilean, Mizpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6241BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6241BZ\"></sup> Joktheel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6241CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6241CA\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Lachish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6242CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6242CB\"></sup> Bozkath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6242CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6242CC\"></sup> Eglon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6242CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6242CD\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Kabbon, Lahmas, Kitlish,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Gederoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6244CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6244CE\"></sup> Beth Dagon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6244CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6244CF\"></sup> Naamah and Makkedah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6244CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6244CG\"></sup>—sixteen towns and their villages.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Libnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6245CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6245CH\"></sup> Ether, Ashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6245CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6245CI\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Iphtah, Ashnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6246CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6246CJ\"></sup> Nezib,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Keilah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6247CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6247CK\"></sup> Akzib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6247CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6247CL\"></sup> and Mareshah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6247CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6247CM\"></sup>—nine towns and their villages.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Ekron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6248CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6248CN\"></sup> with its surrounding settlements and villages;",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>west of Ekron, all that were in the vicinity of Ashdod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6249CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6249CO\"></sup> together with their villages;",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Ashdod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6250CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6250CP\"></sup> its surrounding settlements and villages; and Gaza, its settlements and villages, as far as the Wadi of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6250CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6250CQ\"></sup> and the coastline of the Mediterranean Sea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6250CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6250CR\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>In the hill country:Shamir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6251CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6251CS\"></sup> Jattir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6251CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6251CT\"></sup> Sokoh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6251CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6251CU\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Dannah, Kiriath Sannah (that is, Debir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6252CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6252CV\"></sup>),",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Anab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6253CW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CW&quot;&gt;CW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6253CW\"></sup> Eshtemoh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6253CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6253CX\"></sup> Anim,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Goshen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6254CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6254CY\"></sup> Holon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6254CZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CZ&quot;&gt;CZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6254CZ\"></sup> and Giloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6254DA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DA&quot;&gt;DA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6254DA\"></sup>—eleven towns and their villages.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Arab, Dumah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6255DB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DB&quot;&gt;DB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6255DB\"></sup> Eshan,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Janim, Beth Tappuah, Aphekah,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Humtah, Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6257DC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DC&quot;&gt;DC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6257DC\"></sup> (that is, Hebron) and Zior—nine towns and their villages.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Maon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6258DD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DD&quot;&gt;DD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6258DD\"></sup> Carmel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6258DE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DE&quot;&gt;DE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6258DE\"></sup> Ziph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6258DF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DF&quot;&gt;DF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6258DF\"></sup> Juttah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6258DG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DG&quot;&gt;DG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6258DG\"></sup>",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Jezreel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6259DH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DH&quot;&gt;DH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6259DH\"></sup> Jokdeam, Zanoah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6259DI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DI&quot;&gt;DI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6259DI\"></sup>",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Kain, Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6260DJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DJ&quot;&gt;DJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6260DJ\"></sup> and Timnah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6260DK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DK&quot;&gt;DK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6260DK\"></sup>—ten towns and their villages.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Halhul, Beth Zur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6261DL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DL&quot;&gt;DL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6261DL\"></sup> Gedor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6261DM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DM&quot;&gt;DM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6261DM\"></sup>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Maarath, Beth Anoth and Eltekon—six towns and their villages.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>Kiriath Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6263DN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DN&quot;&gt;DN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6263DN\"></sup> (that is, Kiriath Jearim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6263DO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DO&quot;&gt;DO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6263DO\"></sup>) and Rabbah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6263DP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DP&quot;&gt;DP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6263DP\"></sup>—two towns and their villages.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>In the wilderness:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6264DQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DQ&quot;&gt;DQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6264DQ\"></sup>Beth Arabah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6264DR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DR&quot;&gt;DR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6264DR\"></sup> Middin, Sekakah,",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Nibshan, the City of Salt and En Gedi<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6265DS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DS&quot;&gt;DS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6265DS\"></sup>—six towns and their villages.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Judah could not<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6266DT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DT&quot;&gt;DT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6266DT\"></sup> dislodge the Jebusites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6266DU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DU&quot;&gt;DU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6266DU\"></sup>, who were living in Jerusalem;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6266DV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DV&quot;&gt;DV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6266DV\"></sup> to this day the Jebusites live there with the people of Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6266DW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DW&quot;&gt;DW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6266DW\"></sup>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>The allotment for Joseph began at the Jordan, east of the springs of Jericho, and went up from there through the desert<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6267A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6267A\"></sup> into the hill country of Bethel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6267B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6267B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It went on from Bethel (that is, Luz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6268C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6268C\"></sup>), crossed over to the territory of the Arkites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6268D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6268D\"></sup> in Ataroth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6268E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6268E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>descended westward to the territory of the Japhletites as far as the region of Lower Beth Horon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6269F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6269F\"></sup> and on to Gezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6269G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6269G\"></sup> ending at the Mediterranean Sea.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Manasseh and Ephraim, the descendants of Joseph, received their inheritance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6270H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6270H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>This was the territory of Ephraim, according to its clans:The boundary of their inheritance went from Ataroth Addar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6271I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6271I\"></sup> in the east to Upper Beth Horon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6271J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6271J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and continued to the Mediterranean Sea. From Mikmethath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6272K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6272K\"></sup> on the north it curved eastward to Taanath Shiloh, passing by it to Janoah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6272L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6272L\"></sup> on the east.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then it went down from Janoah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6273M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6273M\"></sup> to Ataroth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6273N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6273N\"></sup> and Naarah, touched Jericho and came out at the Jordan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From Tappuah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6274O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6274O\"></sup> the border went west to the Kanah Ravine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6274P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6274P\"></sup> and ended at the Mediterranean Sea. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the Ephraimites, according to its clans.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It also included all the towns and their villages that were set aside for the Ephraimites within the inheritance of the Manassites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6275Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6275Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They did not dislodge the Canaanites living in Gezer; to this day the Canaanites live among the people of Ephraim but are required to do forced labor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6276R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6276R\"></sup>"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>This was the allotment for the tribe of Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6277A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6277A\"></sup> as Joseph’s firstborn,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6277B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6277B\"></sup> that is, for Makir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6277C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6277C\"></sup> Manasseh’s firstborn. Makir was the ancestor of the Gileadites, who had received Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6277D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6277D\"></sup> and Bashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6277E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6277E\"></sup> because the Makirites were great soldiers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So this allotment was for the rest of the people of Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6278F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6278F\"></sup>—the clans of Abiezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6278G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6278G\"></sup> Helek, Asriel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6278H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6278H\"></sup> Shechem, Hepher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6278I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6278I\"></sup> and Shemida.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6278J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6278J\"></sup> These are the other male descendants of Manasseh son of Joseph by their clans.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Zelophehad son of Hepher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6279K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6279K\"></sup> the son of Gilead, the son of Makir, the son of Manasseh, had no sons but only daughters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6279L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6279L\"></sup> whose names were Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milkah and Tirzah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They went to Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the leaders and said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses to give us an inheritance among our relatives.” So Joshua gave them an inheritance along with the brothers of their father, according to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6280M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6280M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Manasseh’s share consisted of ten tracts of land besides Gilead and Bashan east of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6281N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6281N\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>because the daughters of the tribe of Manasseh received an inheritance among the sons. The land of Gilead belonged to the rest of the descendants of Manasseh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The territory of Manasseh extended from Asher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6283O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6283O\"></sup> to Mikmethath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6283P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6283P\"></sup> east of Shechem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6283Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6283Q\"></sup> The boundary ran southward from there to include the people living at En Tappuah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>(Manasseh had the land of Tappuah, but Tappuah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6284R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6284R\"></sup> itself, on the boundary of Manasseh, belonged to the Ephraimites.)",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the boundary continued south to the Kanah Ravine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6285S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6285S\"></sup> There were towns belonging to Ephraim lying among the towns of Manasseh, but the boundary of Manasseh was the northern side of the ravine and ended at the Mediterranean Sea.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On the south the land belonged to Ephraim, on the north to Manasseh. The territory of Manasseh reached the Mediterranean Sea and bordered Asher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6286T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6286T\"></sup> on the north and Issachar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6286U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6286U\"></sup> on the east.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6286V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6286V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Within Issachar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287W\"></sup> and Asher, Manasseh also had Beth Shan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287X\"></sup> Ibleam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287Y\"></sup> and the people of Dor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287Z\"></sup> Endor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287AA\"></sup> Taanach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287AB\"></sup> and Megiddo,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287AC\"></sup> together with their surrounding settlements (the third in the list is Naphoth).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6287AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6287AD\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Yet the Manassites were not able<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6288AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6288AE\"></sup> to occupy these towns, for the Canaanites were determined to live in that region.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>However, when the Israelites grew stronger, they subjected the Canaanites to forced labor but did not drive them out completely.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6289AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6289AF\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The people of Joseph said to Joshua, “Why have you given us only one allotment and one portion for an inheritance? We are a numerous people, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed us abundantly.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6290AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6290AG\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“If you are so numerous,” Joshua answered, “and if the hill country of Ephraim is too small for you, go up into the forest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6291AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6291AH\"></sup> and clear land for yourselves there in the land of the Perizzites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6291AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6291AI\"></sup> and Rephaites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6291AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6291AJ\"></sup>”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The people of Joseph replied, “The hill country is not enough for us, and all the Canaanites who live in the plain have chariots fitted with iron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6292AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6292AK\"></sup> both those in Beth Shan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6292AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6292AL\"></sup> and its settlements and those in the Valley of Jezreel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6292AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6292AM\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Joshua said to the tribes of Joseph—to Ephraim and Manasseh—“You are numerous and very powerful. You will have not only one allotment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6293AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6293AN\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>but the forested hill country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6294AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6294AO\"></sup> as well. Clear it, and its farthest limits will be yours; though the Canaanites have chariots fitted with iron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6294AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6294AP\"></sup> and though they are strong, you can drive them out.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>The whole assembly of the Israelites gathered at Shiloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6295A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6295A\"></sup> and set up the tent of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6295B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6295B\"></sup> there. The country was brought under their control,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>but there were still seven Israelite tribes who had not yet received their inheritance.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Joshua said to the Israelites: “How long will you wait before you begin to take possession of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your ancestors, has given you?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Appoint three men from each tribe. I will send them out to make a survey of the land and to write a description of it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6298C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6298C\"></sup> according to the inheritance of each.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6298D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6298D\"></sup> Then they will return to me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You are to divide the land into seven parts. Judah is to remain in its territory on the south<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6299E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6299E\"></sup> and the tribes of Joseph in their territory on the north.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6299F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6299F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After you have written descriptions of the seven parts of the land, bring them here to me and I will cast lots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6300G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6300G\"></sup> for you in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Levites, however, do not get a portion among you, because the priestly service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is their inheritance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6301H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6301H\"></sup> And Gad, Reuben and the half-tribe of Manasseh have already received their inheritance on the east side of the Jordan. Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave it to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6301I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6301I\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As the men started on their way to map out the land, Joshua instructed them, “Go and make a survey of the land and write a description of it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6302J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6302J\"></sup> Then return to me, and I will cast lots for you here at Shiloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6302K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6302K\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the men left and went through the land. They wrote its description on a scroll, town by town, in seven parts, and returned to Joshua in the camp at Shiloh.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Joshua then cast lots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6304L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6304L\"></sup> for them in Shiloh in the presence<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6304M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6304M\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and there he distributed the land to the Israelites according to their tribal divisions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6304N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6304N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The first lot came up for the tribe of Benjamin according to its clans. Their allotted territory lay between the tribes of Judah and Joseph:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>On the north side their boundary began at the Jordan, passed the northern slope of Jericho and headed west into the hill country, coming out at the wilderness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6306O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6306O\"></sup> of Beth Aven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6306P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6306P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From there it crossed to the south slope of Luz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6307Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6307Q\"></sup> (that is, Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6307R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6307R\"></sup>) and went down to Ataroth Addar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6307S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6307S\"></sup> on the hill south of Lower Beth Horon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From the hill facing Beth Horon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6308T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6308T\"></sup> on the south the boundary turned south along the western side and came out at Kiriath Baal (that is, Kiriath Jearim),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6308U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6308U\"></sup> a town of the people of Judah. This was the western side.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The southern side began at the outskirts of Kiriath Jearim on the west, and the boundary came out at the spring of the waters of Nephtoah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6309V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6309V\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The boundary went down to the foot of the hill facing the Valley of Ben Hinnom, north of the Valley of Rephaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6310W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6310W\"></sup> It continued down the Hinnom Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6310X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6310X\"></sup> along the southern slope of the Jebusite city and so to En Rogel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6310Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6310Y\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It then curved north, went to En Shemesh, continued to Geliloth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6311Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6311Z\"></sup> which faces the Pass of Adummim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6311AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6311AA\"></sup> and ran down to the Stone of Bohan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6311AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6311AB\"></sup> son of Reuben.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It continued to the northern slope of Beth Arabah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6312AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6312AC\"></sup> and on down into the Arabah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6312AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6312AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It then went to the northern slope of Beth Hoglah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6313AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6313AE\"></sup> and came out at the northern bay of the Dead Sea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6313AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6313AF\"></sup> at the mouth of the Jordan in the south. This was the southern boundary.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The Jordan formed the boundary on the eastern side.These were the boundaries that marked out the inheritance of the clans of Benjamin on all sides.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6314AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6314AG\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The tribe of Benjamin, according to its clans, had the following towns:Jericho, Beth Hoglah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6315AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6315AH\"></sup> Emek Keziz,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Beth Arabah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6316AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6316AI\"></sup> Zemaraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6316AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6316AJ\"></sup> Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6316AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6316AK\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Avvim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6317AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6317AL\"></sup> Parah, Ophrah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6317AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6317AM\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Kephar Ammoni, Ophni and Geba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6318AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6318AN\"></sup>—twelve towns and their villages.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Gibeon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6319AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6319AO\"></sup> Ramah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6319AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6319AP\"></sup> Beeroth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6319AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6319AQ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Mizpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6320AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6320AR\"></sup> Kephirah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6320AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6320AS\"></sup> Mozah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Rekem, Irpeel, Taralah,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Zelah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6322AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6322AT\"></sup> Haeleph, the Jebusite city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6322AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6322AU\"></sup> (that is, Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6322AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6322AV\"></sup>), Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6322AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6322AW\"></sup> and Kiriath—fourteen towns and their villages.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6322AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6322AX\"></sup>This was the inheritance of Benjamin for its clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6322AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6322AY\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>The second lot came out for the tribe of Simeon according to its clans. Their inheritance lay within the territory of Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6323B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6323B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It included:Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6324C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6324C\"></sup> (or Sheba), Moladah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6324D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6324D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Hazar Shual,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6325E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6325E\"></sup> Balah, Ezem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6325F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6325F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Eltolad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6326G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6326G\"></sup> Bethul, Hormah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6326H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6326H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6327I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6327I\"></sup> Beth Markaboth, Hazar Susah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Beth Lebaoth and Sharuhen—thirteen towns and their villages;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Ain, Rimmon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6329J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6329J\"></sup> Ether and Ashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6329K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6329K\"></sup>—four towns and their villages—",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and all the villages around these towns as far as Baalath Beer (Ramah in the Negev).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6330L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6330L\"></sup>This was the inheritance of the tribe of the Simeonites, according to its clans.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The inheritance of the Simeonites was taken from the share of Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6331M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6331M\"></sup> because Judah’s portion was more than they needed. So the Simeonites received their inheritance within the territory of Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6331N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6331N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The third lot came up for Zebulun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6332O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6332O\"></sup> according to its clans:The boundary of their inheritance went as far as Sarid.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6332P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6332P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Going west it ran to Maralah, touched Dabbesheth, and extended to the ravine near Jokneam.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6333Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6333Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It turned east from Sarid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6334R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6334R\"></sup> toward the sunrise to the territory of Kisloth Tabor and went on to Daberath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6334S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6334S\"></sup> and up to Japhia.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then it continued eastward to Gath Hepher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6335T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6335T\"></sup> and Eth Kazin; it came out at Rimmon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6335U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6335U\"></sup> and turned toward Neah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There the boundary went around on the north to Hannathon and ended at the Valley of Iphtah El.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6336V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6336V\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Included were Kattath, Nahalal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6337W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6337W\"></sup> Shimron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6337X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6337X\"></sup> Idalah and Bethlehem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6337Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6337Y\"></sup> There were twelve towns and their villages.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These towns and their villages were the inheritance of Zebulun,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6338Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6338Z\"></sup> according to its clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6338AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6338AA\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The fourth lot came out for Issachar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6339AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6339AB\"></sup> according to its clans.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Their territory included:Jezreel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6340AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6340AC\"></sup> Kesulloth, Shunem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6340AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6340AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Hapharaim, Shion, Anaharath,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Rabbith, Kishion,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6342AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6342AE\"></sup> Ebez,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Remeth, En Gannim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6343AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6343AF\"></sup> En Haddah and Beth Pazzez.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The boundary touched Tabor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6344AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6344AG\"></sup> Shahazumah and Beth Shemesh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6344AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6344AH\"></sup> and ended at the Jordan. There were sixteen towns and their villages.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These towns and their villages were the inheritance of the tribe of Issachar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6345AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6345AI\"></sup> according to its clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6345AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6345AJ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The fifth lot came out for the tribe of Asher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6346AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6346AK\"></sup> according to its clans.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Their territory included:Helkath, Hali, Beten, Akshaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6347AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6347AL\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Allammelek, Amad and Mishal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6348AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6348AM\"></sup> On the west the boundary touched Carmel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6348AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6348AN\"></sup> and Shihor Libnath.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It then turned east toward Beth Dagon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6349AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6349AO\"></sup> touched Zebulun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6349AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6349AP\"></sup> and the Valley of Iphtah El,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6349AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6349AQ\"></sup> and went north to Beth Emek and Neiel, passing Kabul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6349AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6349AR\"></sup> on the left.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It went to Abdon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6350AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6350AS\"></sup> Rehob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6350AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6350AT\"></sup> Hammon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6350AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6350AU\"></sup> and Kanah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6350AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6350AV\"></sup> as far as Greater Sidon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6350AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6350AW\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The boundary then turned back toward Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6351AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6351AX\"></sup> and went to the fortified city of Tyre,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6351AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6351AY\"></sup> turned toward Hosah and came out at the Mediterranean Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6351AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6351AZ\"></sup> in the region of Akzib,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6351BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6351BA\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Ummah, Aphek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6352BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6352BB\"></sup> and Rehob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6352BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6352BC\"></sup> There were twenty-two towns and their villages.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These towns and their villages were the inheritance of the tribe of Asher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6353BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6353BD\"></sup> according to its clans.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The sixth lot came out for Naphtali according to its clans:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Their boundary went from Heleph and the large tree in Zaanannim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6355BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6355BE\"></sup> passing Adami Nekeb and Jabneel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6355BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6355BF\"></sup> to Lakkum and ending at the Jordan.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The boundary ran west through Aznoth Tabor and came out at Hukkok.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6356BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6356BG\"></sup> It touched Zebulun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6356BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6356BH\"></sup> on the south, Asher on the west and the Jordan on the east.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The fortified towns were Ziddim, Zer, Hammath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6357BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6357BI\"></sup> Rakkath, Kinnereth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6357BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6357BJ\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Adamah, Ramah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6358BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6358BK\"></sup> Hazor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6358BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6358BL\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Kedesh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6359BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6359BM\"></sup> Edrei,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6359BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6359BN\"></sup> En Hazor,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Iron, Migdal El, Horem, Beth Anath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6360BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6360BO\"></sup> and Beth Shemesh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6360BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6360BP\"></sup> There were nineteen towns and their villages.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>These towns and their villages were the inheritance of the tribe of Naphtali, according to its clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6361BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6361BQ\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The seventh lot came out for the tribe of Dan according to its clans.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The territory of their inheritance included:Zorah, Eshtaol,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6363BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6363BR\"></sup> Ir Shemesh,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Shaalabbin, Aijalon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6364BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6364BS\"></sup> Ithlah,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Elon, Timnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6365BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6365BT\"></sup> Ekron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6365BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6365BU\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Eltekeh, Gibbethon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6366BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6366BV\"></sup> Baalath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6366BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6366BW\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Jehud, Bene Berak, Gath Rimmon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6367BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6367BX\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Me Jarkon and Rakkon, with the area facing Joppa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6368BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6368BY\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>(When the territory of the Danites was lost to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6369BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6369BZ\"></sup> they went up and attacked Leshem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6369CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6369CA\"></sup>, took it, put it to the sword and occupied it. They settled in Leshem and named<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6369CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6369CB\"></sup> it Dan after their ancestor.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6369CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6369CC\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>These towns and their villages were the inheritance of the tribe of Dan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6370CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6370CD\"></sup> according to its clans.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>When they had finished dividing the land into its allotted portions, the Israelites gave Joshua son of Nun an inheritance among them,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded. They gave him the town he asked for—Timnath Serah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6372CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6372CE\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim. And he built up the town and settled there.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>These are the territories that Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun and the heads of the tribal clans of Israel assigned by lot at Shiloh in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the entrance to the tent of meeting. And so they finished dividing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6373CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6373CF\"></sup> the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6373CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6373CG\"></sup>"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Tell the Israelites to designate the cities of refuge, as I instructed you through Moses,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>so that anyone who kills a person accidentally and unintentionally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6376B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6376B\"></sup> may flee there and find protection from the avenger of blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6376C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6376C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When they flee to one of these cities, they are to stand in the entrance of the city gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6377D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6377D\"></sup> and state their case before the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6377E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6377E\"></sup> of that city. Then the elders are to admit the fugitive into their city and provide a place to live among them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If the avenger of blood comes in pursuit, the elders must not surrender the fugitive, because the fugitive killed their neighbor unintentionally and without malice aforethought.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They are to stay in that city until they have stood trial before the assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6379F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6379F\"></sup> and until the death of the high priest who is serving at that time. Then they may go back to their own home in the town from which they fled.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they set apart Kedesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6380G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6380G\"></sup> in Galilee in the hill country of Naphtali, Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6380H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6380H\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim, and Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6380I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6380I\"></sup> (that is, Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6380J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6380J\"></sup>) in the hill country of Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6380K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6380K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>East of the Jordan (on the other side from Jericho) they designated Bezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6381L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6381L\"></sup> in the wilderness on the plateau in the tribe of Reuben, Ramoth in Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6381M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6381M\"></sup> in the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6381N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6381N\"></sup> in the tribe of Manasseh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Any of the Israelites or any foreigner residing among them who killed someone accidentally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6382O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6382O\"></sup> could flee to these designated cities and not be killed by the avenger of blood prior to standing trial before the assembly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6382P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6382P\"></sup>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now the family heads of the Levites approached Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the heads of the other tribal families of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6383B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6383B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>at Shiloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6384C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6384C\"></sup> in Canaan and said to them, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded through Moses that you give us towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6384D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6384D\"></sup> to live in, with pasturelands for our livestock.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6384E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6384E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded, the Israelites gave the Levites the following towns and pasturelands out of their own inheritance:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The first lot came out for the Kohathites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6386F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6386F\"></sup> according to their clans. The Levites who were descendants of Aaron the priest were allotted thirteen towns from the tribes of Judah, Simeon and Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6386G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6386G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The rest of Kohath’s descendants were allotted ten towns from the clans of the tribes of Ephraim, Dan and half of Manasseh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6387H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6387H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The descendants of Gershon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6388I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6388I\"></sup> were allotted thirteen towns from the clans of the tribes of Issachar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6388J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6388J\"></sup> Asher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6388K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6388K\"></sup> Naphtali and the half-tribe of Manasseh in Bashan.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The descendants of Merari,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6389L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6389L\"></sup> according to their clans, received twelve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6389M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6389M\"></sup> towns from the tribes of Reuben, Gad and Zebulun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6389N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6389N\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the Israelites allotted to the Levites these towns and their pasturelands, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>From the tribes of Judah and Simeon they allotted the following towns by name",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>(these towns were assigned to the descendants of Aaron who were from the Kohathite clans of the Levites, because the first lot fell to them):",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They gave them Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6393O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6393O\"></sup> (that is, Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6393P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6393P\"></sup>), with its surrounding pastureland, in the hill country of Judah. (Arba was the forefather of Anak.)",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the fields and villages around the city they had given to Caleb son of Jephunneh as his possession.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6394Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6394Q\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So to the descendants of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron (a city of refuge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6395R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6395R\"></sup> for one accused of murder), Libnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6395S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6395S\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jattir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6396T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6396T\"></sup> Eshtemoa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6396U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6396U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Holon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6397V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6397V\"></sup> Debir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6397W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6397W\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Ain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6398X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6398X\"></sup> Juttah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6398Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6398Y\"></sup> and Beth Shemesh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6398Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6398Z\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—nine towns from these two tribes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And from the tribe of Benjamin they gave them Gibeon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6399AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6399AA\"></sup> Geba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6399AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6399AB\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Anathoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6400AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6400AC\"></sup> and Almon, together with their pasturelands—four towns.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The total number of towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6401AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6401AD\"></sup> for the priests, the descendants of Aaron, came to thirteen, together with their pasturelands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6401AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6401AE\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The rest of the Kohathite clans of the Levites were allotted towns from the tribe of Ephraim:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>In the hill country of Ephraim they were given Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6403AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6403AF\"></sup> (a city of refuge for one accused of murder) and Gezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6403AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6403AG\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Kibzaim and Beth Horon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6404AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6404AH\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6404AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6404AI\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Also from the tribe of Dan they received Eltekeh, Gibbethon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6405AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6405AJ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Aijalon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6406AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6406AK\"></sup> and Gath Rimmon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6406AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6406AL\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>From half the tribe of Manasseh they received Taanach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6407AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6407AM\"></sup> and Gath Rimmon, together with their pasturelands—two towns.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>All these ten towns and their pasturelands were given to the rest of the Kohathite clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6408AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6408AN\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The Levite clans of the Gershonites were given:from the half-tribe of Manasseh,Golan in Bashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6409AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6409AO\"></sup> (a city of refuge for one accused of murder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6409AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6409AP\"></sup>) and Be Eshterah, together with their pasturelands—two towns;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>from the tribe of Issachar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6410AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6410AQ\"></sup>Kishion,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6410AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6410AR\"></sup> Daberath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6410AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6410AS\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jarmuth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6411AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6411AT\"></sup> and En Gannim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6411AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6411AU\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>from the tribe of Asher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6412AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6412AV\"></sup>Mishal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6412AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6412AW\"></sup> Abdon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6412AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6412AX\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Helkath and Rehob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6413AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6413AY\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>from the tribe of Naphtali,Kedesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6414AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6414AZ\"></sup> in Galilee (a city of refuge for one accused of murder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6414BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6414BA\"></sup>), Hammoth Dor and Kartan, together with their pasturelands—three towns.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The total number of towns of the Gershonite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6415BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6415BB\"></sup> clans came to thirteen, together with their pasturelands.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The Merarite clans (the rest of the Levites) were given:from the tribe of Zebulun,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6416BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6416BC\"></sup>Jokneam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6416BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6416BD\"></sup> Kartah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Dimnah and Nahalal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6417BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6417BE\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>from the tribe of Reuben,Bezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6418BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6418BF\"></sup> Jahaz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6418BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6418BG\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Kedemoth and Mephaath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6419BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6419BH\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>from the tribe of Gad,Ramoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6420BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6420BI\"></sup> in Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6420BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6420BJ\"></sup> (a city of refuge for one accused of murder), Mahanaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6420BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6420BK\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Heshbon and Jazer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6421BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6421BL\"></sup> together with their pasturelands—four towns in all.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The total number of towns allotted to the Merarite clans, who were the rest of the Levites, came to twelve.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6422BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6422BM\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The towns of the Levites in the territory held by the Israelites were forty-eight in all, together with their pasturelands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6423BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6423BN\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Each of these towns had pasturelands surrounding it; this was true for all these towns.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Israel all the land he had sworn to give their ancestors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6425BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6425BO\"></sup> and they took possession<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6425BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6425BP\"></sup> of it and settled there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6425BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6425BQ\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6426BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6426BR\"></sup> on every side, just as he had sworn to their ancestors. Not one of their enemies<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6426BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6426BS\"></sup> withstood them; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave all their enemies<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6426BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6426BT\"></sup> into their hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6426BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6426BU\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Not one of all the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s good promises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6427BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6427BV\"></sup> to Israel failed; every one was fulfilled."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Then Joshua summoned the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and said to them, “You have done all that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6429A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6429A\"></sup> and you have obeyed me in everything I commanded.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For a long time now—to this very day—you have not deserted your fellow Israelites but have carried out the mission the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gave you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given them rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6431B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6431B\"></sup> as he promised, return to your homes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6431C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6431C\"></sup> in the land that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave you on the other side of the Jordan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6431D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6431D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But be very careful to keep the commandment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6432E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6432E\"></sup> and the law that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave you: to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6432F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6432F\"></sup> your God, to walk in obedience to him, to keep his commands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6432G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6432G\"></sup> to hold fast to him and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6432H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6432H\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Joshua blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6433I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6433I\"></sup> them and sent them away, and they went to their homes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>(To the half-tribe of Manasseh Moses had given land in Bashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6434J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6434J\"></sup> and to the other half of the tribe Joshua gave land on the west side<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6434K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6434K\"></sup> of the Jordan along with their fellow Israelites.) When Joshua sent them home, he blessed them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6434L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6434L\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>saying, “Return to your homes with your great wealth—with large herds of livestock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6435M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6435M\"></sup> with silver, gold, bronze and iron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6435N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6435N\"></sup> and a great quantity of clothing—and divide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6435O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6435O\"></sup> the plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6435P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6435P\"></sup> from your enemies with your fellow Israelites.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh left the Israelites at Shiloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6436Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6436Q\"></sup> in Canaan to return to Gilead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6436R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6436R\"></sup> their own land, which they had acquired in accordance with the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When they came to Geliloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6437S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6437S\"></sup> near the Jordan in the land of Canaan, the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh built an imposing altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6437T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6437T\"></sup> there by the Jordan.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And when the Israelites heard that they had built the altar on the border of Canaan at Geliloth near the Jordan on the Israelite side,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the whole assembly of Israel gathered at Shiloh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6439U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6439U\"></sup> to go to war against them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the Israelites sent Phinehas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6440V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6440V\"></sup> son of Eleazar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6440W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6440W\"></sup> the priest, to the land of Gilead—to Reuben, Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>With him they sent ten of the chief men, one from each of the tribes of Israel, each the head of a family division among the Israelite clans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6441X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6441X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When they went to Gilead—to Reuben, Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh—they said to them:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“The whole assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘How could you break faith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6443Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6443Y\"></sup> with the God of Israel like this? How could you turn away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and build yourselves an altar in rebellion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6443Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6443Z\"></sup> against him now?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Was not the sin of Peor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6444AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6444AA\"></sup> enough for us? Up to this very day we have not cleansed ourselves from that sin, even though a plague fell on the community of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And are you now turning away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?“‘If you rebel against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> today, tomorrow he will be angry with the whole community<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6445AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6445AB\"></sup> of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If the land you possess is defiled, come over to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s land, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s tabernacle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6446AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6446AC\"></sup> stands, and share the land with us. But do not rebel against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> or against us by building an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6446AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6446AD\"></sup> for yourselves, other than the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Achan son of Zerah was unfaithful in regard to the devoted things,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6447AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6447AE\"></sup> did not wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6447AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6447AF\"></sup> come on the whole community<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6447AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6447AG\"></sup> of Israel? He was not the only one who died for his sin.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6447AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6447AH\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Reuben, Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh replied to the heads of the clans of Israel:",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“The Mighty One, God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! The Mighty One, God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6449AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6449AI\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6449AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6449AJ\"></sup> He knows!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6449AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6449AK\"></sup> And let Israel know! If this has been in rebellion or disobedience to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do not spare us this day.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>If we have built our own altar to turn away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to offer burnt offerings and grain offerings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6450AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6450AL\"></sup> or to sacrifice fellowship offerings on it, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself call us to account.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6450AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6450AM\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“No! We did it for fear that some day your descendants might say to ours, ‘What do you have to do with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made the Jordan a boundary between us and you—you Reubenites and Gadites! You have no share in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’ So your descendants might cause ours to stop fearing the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“That is why we said, ‘Let us get ready and build an altar—but not for burnt offerings or sacrifices.’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>On the contrary, it is to be a witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6454AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6454AN\"></sup> between us and you and the generations that follow, that we will worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at his sanctuary with our burnt offerings, sacrifices and fellowship offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6454AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6454AO\"></sup> Then in the future your descendants will not be able to say to ours, ‘You have no share in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“And we said, ‘If they ever say this to us, or to our descendants, we will answer: Look at the replica of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s altar, which our ancestors built, not for burnt offerings and sacrifices, but as a witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6455AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6455AP\"></sup> between us and you.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Far be it from us to rebel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6456AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6456AQ\"></sup> against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and turn away from him today by building an altar for burnt offerings, grain offerings and sacrifices, other than the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God that stands before his tabernacle.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6456AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6456AR\"></sup>”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When Phinehas the priest and the leaders of the community—the heads of the clans of the Israelites—heard what Reuben, Gad and Manasseh had to say, they were pleased.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Phinehas son of Eleazar, the priest, said to Reuben, Gad and Manasseh, “Today we know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6458AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6458AS\"></sup> because you have not been unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in this matter. Now you have rescued the Israelites from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s hand.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then Phinehas son of Eleazar, the priest, and the leaders returned to Canaan from their meeting with the Reubenites and Gadites in Gilead and reported to the Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6459AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6459AT\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They were glad to hear the report and praised God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6460AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6460AU\"></sup> And they talked no more about going to war against them to devastate the country where the Reubenites and the Gadites lived.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And the Reubenites and the Gadites gave the altar this name: A Witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6461AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6461AV\"></sup> Between Us—that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>After a long time had passed and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given Israel rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6462A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6462A\"></sup> from all their enemies around them, Joshua, by then a very old man,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6462B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6462B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>summoned all Israel—their elders,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6463C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6463C\"></sup> leaders, judges and officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6463D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6463D\"></sup>—and said to them: “I am very old.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6463E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6463E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You yourselves have seen everything the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has done to all these nations for your sake; it was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who fought for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6464F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6464F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Remember how I have allotted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6465G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6465G\"></sup> as an inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6465H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6465H\"></sup> for your tribes all the land of the nations that remain—the nations I conquered—between the Jordan and the Mediterranean Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6465I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6465I\"></sup> in the west.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God himself will push them out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6466J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6466J\"></sup> for your sake. He will drive them out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6466K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6466K\"></sup> before you, and you will take possession of their land, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God promised you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6466L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6466L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Be very strong; be careful to obey all that is written in the Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6467M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6467M\"></sup> of Moses, without turning aside<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6467N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6467N\"></sup> to the right or to the left.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6467O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6467O\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Do not associate with these nations that remain among you; do not invoke the names of their gods or swear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6468P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6468P\"></sup> by them. You must not serve them or bow down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6468Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6468Q\"></sup> to them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But you are to hold fast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6469R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6469R\"></sup> your God, as you have until now.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has driven out before you great and powerful nations;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6470S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6470S\"></sup> to this day no one has been able to withstand you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6470T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6470T\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>One of you routs a thousand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6471U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6471U\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God fights for you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6471V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6471V\"></sup> just as he promised.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So be very careful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6472W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6472W\"></sup> to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6472X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6472X\"></sup> your God.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“But if you turn away and ally yourselves with the survivors of these nations that remain among you and if you intermarry with them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6473Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6473Y\"></sup> and associate with them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6473Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6473Z\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>then you may be sure that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will no longer drive out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6474AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6474AA\"></sup> these nations before you. Instead, they will become snares<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6474AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6474AB\"></sup> and traps for you, whips on your backs and thorns in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6474AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6474AC\"></sup> until you perish from this good land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6474AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6474AD\"></sup> which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Now I am about to go the way of all the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6475AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6475AE\"></sup> You know with all your heart and soul that not one of all the good promises the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gave you has failed. Every promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6475AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6475AF\"></sup> has been fulfilled; not one has failed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6475AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6475AG\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But just as all the good things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6476AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6476AH\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has promised you have come to you, so he will bring on you all the evil things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6476AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6476AI\"></sup> he has threatened, until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has destroyed you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6476AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6476AJ\"></sup> from this good land he has given you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6476AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6476AK\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If you violate the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which he commanded you, and go and serve other gods and bow down to them, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger will burn against you, and you will quickly perish from the good land he has given you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6477AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6477AL\"></sup>”"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Then Joshua assembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6478A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6478A\"></sup> all the tribes of Israel at Shechem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6478B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6478B\"></sup> He summoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6478C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6478C\"></sup> the elders,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6478D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6478D\"></sup> leaders, judges and officials of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6478E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6478E\"></sup> and they presented themselves before God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joshua said to all the people, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: ‘Long ago your ancestors, including Terah the father of Abraham and Nahor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6479F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6479F\"></sup> lived beyond the Euphrates River and worshiped other gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6479G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6479G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But I took your father Abraham from the land beyond the Euphrates and led him throughout Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6480H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6480H\"></sup> and gave him many descendants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6480I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6480I\"></sup> I gave him Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6480J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6480J\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and to Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6481K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6481K\"></sup> I assigned the hill country of Seir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6481L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6481L\"></sup> to Esau, but Jacob and his family went down to Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6481M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6481M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“‘Then I sent Moses and Aaron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6482N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6482N\"></sup> and I afflicted the Egyptians by what I did there, and I brought you out.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6482O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6482O\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When I brought your people out of Egypt, you came to the sea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6483P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6483P\"></sup> and the Egyptians pursued them with chariots and horsemen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6483Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6483Q\"></sup> as far as the Red Sea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6483R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6483R\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But they cried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6484S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6484S\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for help, and he put darkness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6484T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6484T\"></sup> between you and the Egyptians; he brought the sea over them and covered them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6484U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6484U\"></sup> You saw with your own eyes what I did to the Egyptians.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6484V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6484V\"></sup> Then you lived in the wilderness for a long time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6484W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6484W\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘I brought you to the land of the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6485X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6485X\"></sup> who lived east of the Jordan. They fought against you, but I gave them into your hands. I destroyed them from before you, and you took possession of their land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6485Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6485Y\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Balak son of Zippor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6486Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6486Z\"></sup> the king of Moab, prepared to fight against Israel, he sent for Balaam son of Beor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6486AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6486AA\"></sup> to put a curse on you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6486AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6486AB\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But I would not listen to Balaam, so he blessed you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6487AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6487AC\"></sup> again and again, and I delivered you out of his hand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘Then you crossed the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6488AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6488AD\"></sup> and came to Jericho.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6488AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6488AE\"></sup> The citizens of Jericho fought against you, as did also the Amorites, Perizzites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6488AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6488AF\"></sup> Canaanites, Hittites, Girgashites, Hivites and Jebusites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6488AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6488AG\"></sup> but I gave them into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6488AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6488AH\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I sent the hornet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6489AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6489AI\"></sup> ahead of you, which drove them out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6489AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6489AJ\"></sup> before you—also the two Amorite kings. You did not do it with your own sword and bow.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6489AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6489AK\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So I gave you a land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6490AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6490AL\"></sup> on which you did not toil and cities you did not build; and you live in them and eat from vineyards and olive groves that you did not plant.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6490AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6490AM\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Now fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6491AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6491AN\"></sup> and serve him with all faithfulness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6491AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6491AO\"></sup> Throw away the gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6491AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6491AP\"></sup> your ancestors worshiped beyond the Euphrates River and in Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6491AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6491AQ\"></sup> and serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But if serving the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> seems undesirable to you, then choose for yourselves this day whom you will serve, whether the gods your ancestors served beyond the Euphrates, or the gods of the Amorites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6492AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6492AR\"></sup> in whose land you are living. But as for me and my household,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6492AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6492AS\"></sup> we will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6492AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6492AT\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the people answered, “Far be it from us to forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6493AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6493AU\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to serve other gods!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God himself who brought us and our parents up out of Egypt, from that land of slavery,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6494AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6494AV\"></sup> and performed those great signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6494AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6494AW\"></sup> before our eyes. He protected us on our entire journey and among all the nations through which we traveled.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6495AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6495AX\"></sup> before us all the nations,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6495AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6495AY\"></sup> including the Amorites, who lived in the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6495AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6495AZ\"></sup> We too will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because he is our God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6495BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6495BA\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Joshua said to the people, “You are not able to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He is a holy God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6496BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6496BB\"></sup> he is a jealous God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6496BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6496BC\"></sup> He will not forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6496BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6496BD\"></sup> your rebellion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6496BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6496BE\"></sup> and your sins.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>If you forsake the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6497BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6497BF\"></sup> and serve foreign gods, he will turn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6497BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6497BG\"></sup> and bring disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6497BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6497BH\"></sup> on you and make an end of you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6497BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6497BI\"></sup> after he has been good to you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But the people said to Joshua, “No! We will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Joshua said, “You are witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6499BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6499BJ\"></sup> against yourselves that you have chosen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6499BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6499BK\"></sup> to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”“Yes, we are witnesses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6499BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6499BL\"></sup>” they replied.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Now then,” said Joshua, “throw away the foreign gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6500BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6500BM\"></sup> that are among you and yield your hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6500BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6500BN\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the people said to Joshua, “We will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God and obey him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6501BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6501BO\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>On that day Joshua made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6502BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6502BP\"></sup> for the people, and there at Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6502BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6502BQ\"></sup> he reaffirmed for them decrees and laws.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6502BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6502BR\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Joshua recorded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6503BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6503BS\"></sup> these things in the Book of the Law of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6503BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6503BT\"></sup> Then he took a large stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6503BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6503BU\"></sup> and set it up there under the oak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6503BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6503BV\"></sup> near the holy place of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“See!” he said to all the people. “This stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6504BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6504BW\"></sup> will be a witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6504BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6504BX\"></sup> against us. It has heard all the words the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to us. It will be a witness against you if you are untrue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6504BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6504BY\"></sup> to your God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6504BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6504BZ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Joshua dismissed the people, each to their own inheritance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6505CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6505CA\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>After these things, Joshua son of Nun, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, died<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6506CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6506CC\"></sup> at the age of a hundred and ten.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6506CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6506CD\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And they buried him in the land of his inheritance, at Timnath Serah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6507CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6507CE\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim, north of Mount Gaash.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6507CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6507CF\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Israel served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> throughout the lifetime of Joshua and of the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6508CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6508CG\"></sup> who outlived him and who had experienced everything the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done for Israel.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Joseph’s bones,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6509CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6509CH\"></sup> which the Israelites had brought up from Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6509CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6509CI\"></sup> were buried at Shechem in the tract of land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6509CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6509CJ\"></sup> that Jacob bought for a hundred pieces of silver from the sons of Hamor, the father of Shechem. This became the inheritance of Joseph’s descendants.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Eleazar son of Aaron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6510CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6510CK\"></sup> died and was buried at Gibeah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6510CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6510CL\"></sup> which had been allotted to his son Phinehas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6510CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6510CM\"></sup> in the hill country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6510CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6510CN\"></sup> of Ephraim."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;